title: brown-eyed susans(century-old recipe)
directions: Cream the margarine.
Add sugar, almond extract, flour and salt.
Roll a level tablespoon of mixture into balls.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped tuna
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water for 10 minutes.
Melt butter; blend in flour, seasonings and milk, gradually.
Bring to a boil.

title: coconut jam cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Blend flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Add oats and mix.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in flaked coconut.

title: mocha brownie torte
directions: Blend brownie mix (dry), wate and eggs.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 2 round pans (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan.
Remove from pans and cool thoroughly on wire racks.

title: chicken fried steaks
directions: Put black pepper, garlic powder and meat tenderizer in plastic bag and shake together.
Sprinkle spices over beaten and tenderized meat.
Any leftover spices add to the flour.
Will be used to flour the meat.
Need a large bowl for the buttermilk and eggs.
Whip together.

Dip steak in flour mixture first then egg mixture, then flour mixture again, pressing all the flour you can into the steak. Place in hot oil and fry until steak will float, about 10 to 15 minutes on each side.
Lift out of hot oil with tongs.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir sugar and milk until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to boiling over medium-high heat.
Boil approximately 5 minutes or until mixture is at soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Stir in Marshmallow Creme until dissolved.
Stir in peanut butter until blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in large bowl.
Bring all ingredients, except first two, to a boil in pan, then pour over dry ingredients. Stir until flour is absorbed.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, 2 eggs, 1 teaspoon baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Grease 11 x 14-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese 'n crackers
directions: Place desired number of eggs in pan.
Cover with cold water and bring to a boil.
Turn off heat and allow eggs to sit in hot water for 20 minutes.
Place pan under faucet and run cold water over it for a few minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Measure and sift dry ingredients. Mix molasses and hot water. Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid. Beat after each addition. Bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350°. Makes 16 portions.

title: broccoli bake
directions: If using fresh broccoli, parboil first.
Lay broccoli on bottom of baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Cover with cream of mushroom soup. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over soup and broccoli.
Cover entirely; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Delicious!

title: six weeks muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt shortening in water.
Cool.
Mix sugar, eggs and salt.
Add.
Add buttermilk and baking soda.
Add cereals and flour.
Pour into muffin pans; bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Can store unused batter in refrigerator in a tightly covered container for 6 weeks.

title: meat loaf with pimiento
directions: Combine all ingredients except catsup and noodles.
Shape into loaf.
Place in baking pan and spread top with catsup.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
To serve, place loaf on platter; garnish with pimiento.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of pepper; remove all seeds and membranes from each.
Wash inside and outside.
Cook the peppers in the boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain.

title: butterhorns
directions: Combine flour and ginger; set aside.
Heat milk until scald. Put in mixer bowl; let it cool down to 115°.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar to 1/2 cup warm water; add yeast (regular or fast rise).
Let set a few minutes to dissolve the yeast.
Add about half the flour and one egg to the milk mixture.
Mix well; add yeast and rest of flour and beat for several minutes.
Remove from mixer bowl; work by hand on a floured board until it becomes easy to handle.
Put in greased bowl and cover with a cloth and put in warm place.
Let rise until doubled in size; punch down.
Let rest 20 minutes; grease two cookie sheets.
Roll half the dough in a circle (like pizza).
Butter the dough and cut like pizza.
Roll up from large end to small end; pinch ends and put that side down on cookie sheet.
Do second half and let rise double size.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown; remove from pan to cooling rack. Frost while warm.

title: bitsu - bitsu
directions: Wash, peel and grate sweet potato.
Add flour and sugar. Shape into patties.
Pan-fry until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: classic green bean casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 of the onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until
hot.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 8 1/2 cups or 10 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: ice cream
directions: Using blender, blend together until well mixed.
Serves two people.
For more servings, recipe may be doubled.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread preserves in bottom of pan.
In small bowl, stir together raisins, brown sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients. Beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Spread batter evenly over preserves. Sprinkle with brown sugar mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine margarine, cream cheese and flour in bowl; mix well. Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into small balls.
Press into miniature muffin cups.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Place 1 teaspoon in each prepared muffin cup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Freeze if desired.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: pistachio pesto cheese
directions: In small bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese with pesto sauce and 1/4 cup pistachio.
Spoon into serving dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup pistachios and garnish with basil leaves.

title: oversea fudge
directions: Boil sugar, oleo and Pet milk until forms pretty hard ball. Beat in the chocolate chips, marshmallows and pecans.
Beat until fairly thick.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Makes 3 pounds of candy.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream together the sugar, flour and butter.
Stir in beaten egg yolks.
Add lemon juice, rind and milk slowly.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the mixture.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread out crescent roll dough on 10 x 13-inch cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: pumpkin peach pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Beat eggs.
Add milk and stir into first mixture.
Cook over hot water until it thickens, stirring constantly.
Add butter, pecans and pumpkin. Mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Freezes well, but freeze separately.

title: baked trout supreme
directions: Rinse fish thoroughly.
Use a baking pan or dish.
Pour mushrooms in pan; spread evenly.
Season trout inside and out. Lay trout on top of mushrooms, sliced.
Slice onion and place inside cavity of fish.
Slice margarine or butter and place on top of fish.
Preheat oven to 375° and bake fish for 30 to 45 minutes, until well done.

title: pasta salad #1
directions: Combine vegetables.
Pour dressing over vegetables; cover and marinate at least 3 hours in refrigerator.
Cook spaghetti; drain and chill.
Combine vegetable mixture and chilled spaghetti.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Toss gently to coat.
Sprinkle with bacon bits and additional Parmesan cheese.

title: crabmeat mornay
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onions.
Blend flour, cream and cheese until melted.
Add other ingredients. Gently fold in crabmeat.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chips, margarine and corn syrup in medium size saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla extract and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies cereal, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm and cut.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in large container.
Use 3 heaping tablespoonfuls per cup of boiling water.

title: kathy's pink salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 30 seconds after each.
Stir 1 cup flour into creamed mixture until blended.
Combine buttermilk, soda, salt, lemon extract, vanilla extract and butter flavoring.
Stir 1/2 of buttermilk mixture into creamed mixture until blended. Stir 1 cup flour into creamed mixture, then remaining buttermilk mixture, and end with 1 cup flour.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Don't fill pan too full; it overflows when cooking.

title: mock bloody marys
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter, powdered sugar and graham crackers.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour chips over top and chill.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients, except the sour cream.
Pour half of mixture into 13 x 9-inch pan and refrigerate until set.
Spoon sour cream over set mixture.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Use second snow of the season and make sure snow is clean. Mix milk, sugar, egg and vanilla in large bowl.
Gradually add snow.
Adjust ingredients to taste.

title: easy slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Mix vinegar and sugar with salt and pepper. Mix well.

title: easy corn bread dressing
directions: Boil celery and onion in water then add margarine.
Let cool. Combine corn bread, light bread, broth, celery, onion, sage, salt and pepper.
Add beaten eggs last with flour mixing lightly, but thoroughly.
Spread mixture in baking dish or large pan with non-stick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 to 12 servings.
Dressing is sufficient to stuff a 12 pound turkey.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown meat in bacon drippings.
Add all ingredients plus cooked noodles.
Cook at 350° in covered casserole 45 minutes, then uncover and cook 15 minutes.
Makes 1 large or 2 small casseroles. Freezes well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix salt, egg and cracker meal with ground beef.
Place in loaf pan, then saute in oil celery, onions, peppers, whole tomatoes
and
flour
until
brown.
Then pour over meat loaf. Bake meat loaf in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked crab
directions: Melt butter. Add flour. Stir until smooth.
Pour in milk. Stir until thick. Add salt, pepper, mayonnaise, eggs and crab. Mix well.
Pour into shells or individual casseroles. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook hamburger until done.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup.
Layer tater tots in baking pan.
Lay the cheese and hamburger mixture until all the tater tots, hamburger and soup are used, then top with remaining cheese.
Cook until tater tots are brown and cheese is melted, about 20 minutes.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: You also need 20 cupcake liners.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs and milk.
Mix and sift the flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg with lemon rind. Add to creamed mixture.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
May place raisins or M&M's in center of cookie before baking.
You can also put a dab of jelly on cookies and cover with a teaspoon of dough; then bake.
Remove at once from pan and cool on rack.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 by 9 inch baking dish. Heat 4 cups milk in a medium saucepan just until bubbles form around edge of pan, about 7 min.
Combine warm milk and bread cubes in a medium bowl.
Let stand until cool.
Whisk 3 eggs in a medium bowl.
Stir in sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add bread cube mixture and mix well.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Spoon bread mixture into prepared dish.
Bake until set and lightly browned, about 1 hour. For sauce, combine brown sugar and flour in a medium saucepan.
Stir in remaining milk and remaining eggs. Cook over low heat, stirring continually, until thickened. Drizzle over bread pudding in dessert bowls.

title: pea salad
directions: Cook peas; drain in colander, running cold water over them until they are completely cool.
(You can use fresh peas.) Cover the bottom of a glass rectangular baking dish with broken lettuce. Cover lettuce with onion rings and peas.
(You may also want to try celery or green peppers for a little variety.)
Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise over the lettuce mixture.
Sprinkle mayonnaise with Parmesan cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread beans on a serving dish.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread on top of beans.
Chop tomatoes and green peppers. Sprinkle on top with cheese.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: western onions
directions: Slice onions and soak in solution overnight.
Drain well.
Add Miracle Whip and celery seed to your taste and mix well.
Very good with barbecue.

title: jello pie
directions: Mix the Jell-O with 1 cup hot water and stir until dissolved, then add 1 cup ice.
Stir until thick.
Add peaches, then fold in topping.
Put in crust and refrigerate until set up.

title: chicken and potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion with oil in hot saucepan.
Add chicken, chicken broth, parsley and salt.
Heat to boiling. Lower heat; cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Stir in Pet milk and simmer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli slightly.
Simmer chicken in water until tender. In separate pan, combine soup, mushrooms, nutmeg, Worcestershire, mayo, sherry and curry powder.
Stir over low heat, folding in whipped cream.
Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place layer of broccoli, layer chicken and layer sauce.
Sprinkle liberally with bread crumbs, grated cheese and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly and brown.
Serve with rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend one stick margarine with graham cracker crumbs.
Line bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with this crust.
Beat 2 sticks margarine, sugar and eggs for 15 minutes.
Spread over cracker crumbs and slice bananas over that; then spread pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill in refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.
Also, you can add a layer of fresh strawberries after the layer of pineapple.

title: scrumptious stroganoff
directions: Mix ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Cook mixture on low throughout the day.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Drain and cool in refrigerator.

title: grandma reed's holiday pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugar, then add eggs and water.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in pumpkin, nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 3 large or 6 small loaf pans.
Bake for 65 to 70 minutes, until done.

title: noodle rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add noodles (uncooked). Stir until brown.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add noodles.
Put in a large 3-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crazy cake
directions: Take an 8 x 8 loaf cake pan and sift first 4 ingredients into it without greasing the pan. Make 3 holes in this mixture. Into one hole, pour vanilla. Into the second hole, pour vinegar. Into the third hole, pour melted fat. Over all, pour water. Stir it "like crazy" until well mixed. Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water until tender, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown onion and meats.
Drain.
Add tomato paste and water. Blend all together.
Add tomato puree, sugar and salt.
Cook for about 2 hours on low heat.
Cook 1/2 package of lasagne noodles according to package directions.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli.
Melt remaining ingredients.
Mix with broccoli and almonds.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and oleo by hand.
Pat into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool (300° for 15 minutes).
Mix Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Spread on top of flour mixture.
Prepare pudding with milk.
Put on top of cream cheese layer.
Put rest of large Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: cathy's coffee cake
directions: Make crumbs of above ingredients. Remove 1 c. and to this add 1/2 tsp. cinnamon and 1/4 c. chopped nuts. To the remainder of the crumbs add 1 egg, 1 c. sour cream, and 1 tsp. soda. Mix and pour into 2 - 8 inch cake pans. Top with crumbs and bake at 375° for 25-30 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Blend butter, flour and cream cheese well. Pat into small muffin pans.

title: hot cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, cool, debone and chop into bite-size pieces. Set aside.
In large pot or skillet, melt 3 tablespoons oleo. Cook onions, peppers and mushrooms until soft.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir until melted.
Add undiluted soups, chopped chicken and heat thoroughly.
Cook spaghetti in reserved chicken broth.
Drain.
Layer spaghetti and chicken mixture in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Freezes very well before baking.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spread a little filling on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread filling down middle of each flour tortilla; roll each one up.
(Can sprinkle some cheese on top before rolling up.)
Place seam side down.
Spread rest of filling over tops of tortillas. Sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aloha loaf
directions: Cream margarine or butter with sugar; add eggs and mix well. Stir in mashed bananas. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Stir into creamed mixture. Fold in undrained pineapple and coconut. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until it tests done. Makes 2 loaves. Or use 3 (8 1/4 x 4 1/4-inch) loaf pans and bake 55 minutes.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, egg, cracker crumbs, onion, 1/3 cup tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sugars and beat until combined. Stir in chips. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Place mix on a large piece of plastic wrap and shape into ball. Refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Just before serving on graham crackers, roll in pecans.

title: lemon-broccoli chicken
directions: Cut 4 thin slices of lemon; set aside.
Squeeze 2 teaspoons juice from remaining lemon; set aside.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Put ham in very large pan and cover with water.
Boil at least 2 hours.
Cook onions, carrots and potatoes in broth.
Remove enough broth to cover sliced cabbage and cook until just tender. Do not cook cabbage with ham and vegetables as cabbage taste will penetrate them.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cut beef into small chunks.
Heat a deep pan with olive oil and add onion, stirring frequently, until brown.
Add paprika, 1/4 cup water and beef.
Stir constantly until water evaporates.
Add remaining ingredients, except beef broth.
Mix well.
Add broth as needed to cover all ingredients.
Keep on a slow flame and stir occasionally.
Let beef get tender, about 2 to 3 hours.
Tastes great served over white rice or egg noodles; also with a fresh loaf of bread.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: angel hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine Nestle milk chocolate morsels, butter and corn syrup in a medium saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Add Kellogg's Rice Krispies cereal, mixing lightly until well coated.
Spread evenly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 48 squares.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil, eggs and water. Add bananas.
Add all dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in a
large baking pan, 16 x 10 x 2-inch, and bake at 325° for 30 minutes and then at 300° for 30 minutes or until baked.

title: overnight buns
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and let set for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in very large mixing bowl and let raise.

title: chicken wings teriyaki
directions: Cut wings into three sections.
Tip ends can be cooked for broth.
Marinate overnight in sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix sausage, egg, parsley and onion together.
Cut the pie crust into squares.
Place one teaspoon of mix into each square. Fold together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients; combine with the butter mixture.
Blend well.
Add bananas, sour cream and vanilla; stir well.
Stir in the nuts; pour into a well buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or several smaller pans.
Bake for 1 hour.
Turn out onto a rack to cool.

title: cho-oat-chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts; mix well.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie and 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool 1 minute. Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yields about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: chicago deep dish pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in the warm water. Add flour and salt all at once, mix and then knead into a ball. Drizzle olive oil on dough ball and work into dough. Cover and let double in size.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into pan and bake
for
15 minutes at 350°.
Take 1/2 Cool Whip and mix thoroughly
with cream cheese, then add powdered sugar.
Layer this on
cooled crust, then mix pudding with milk.
Layer this on top of cream
cheese mixture.
Next layer on remaining Cool Whip, then top
with
shaved
chocolate
bar and chopped nuts. Real rich and real good.

title: no-peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease casserole.
Mix first six ingredients and place chicken on top.
Sprinkle chicken with dry onion soup mix.
Seal with foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
This recipe is easily expandable, but don't peek!

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make long sheet cake as directed on box.
Take half of cake and crumble in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Take 1/2 of pudding and smooth on top of cake crumbs. Put 1/2 can cherry pie filling on top of pudding.
Put 1/2 can of crushed pineapple on top of cherries.
Put 8 ounces Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Add crushed nuts.
Take rest of cake and crumble on top of nuts.
Repeat all steps.

title: heavenly eggs crawfish
directions: Saute crawfish, onions and bell pepper in butter until soft. Add tomato sauce and let simmer.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Pour over mixture and cook until moisture has nearly evaporated and eggs are soft.
Add rice mix.
Serve hot.
Shrimp or crabmeat can be used.

title: sunshine chicken salad
directions: Combine dressing mix, mayonnaise, yogurt and honey. Chill for 30 minutes.
Place the remaining ingredients except almonds in a bowl.
Toss with the dressing. Sprinkle with almonds. Serves 4.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; add milk.
Pour over margarine and put fruit in the
top
of
mixture.
Bake
for 30 minutes or until golden brown in a 350° oven.

title: ham and swiss cheese rolls
directions: Put ham and Swiss cheese on rolls.
Put in baking dish.
Mix in pot the butter, mustard, sauce and 1 tablespoon poppy seed. Heat until butter melts.
Pour over rolls; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apricot-pineapple salad
directions: Drain apricots, reserving juice.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add 1 cup apricot juice and 1/2 cup pineapple juice, stirring well.
Add apricots, pineapple and marshmallows; pour mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Chill until set.

title: hurry-up chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger.
Pour off drippings.
Add onion, celery and water.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add bean sprouts.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix beans, uncooked bacon, catsup and brown sugar all together in a large bowl.
Bake uncovered for 2 hours at 300° to 350°.

title: crispy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding 1 egg at a time.
Beat on medium speed 10 to 15 minutes or until very fluffy.
Spoon batter into 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.
To test, insert toothpick; it should come out clean.

title: green bean casserole
directions: To make white sauce, melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and cook 1-2 minutes stirring constantly.
Whish in milk and bring to a boil.
Whisk constantly for 1-2 minutes until thick.
Stir in dressing mix and white pepper and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray skillet with nonstick Pam.
Heat and add onion and garlic (minced).
Cook for 2-3 minutes and set aside.
Add mushrooms to onion mixture and cook additional 5 minutes.
Combine mixture to green beans and add white sauce in casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and cover mixture.
Bake uncovered for 20-30 minutes.

title: herbed honey lime sauce
directions: Saute onion in olive oil.
Add wine, honey, lime juice, mustard, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil. Combine cornstarch and water.
Mix well and add to sauce.
Cook and stir until sauce thickens.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve over cooked turkey, chicken, fish or pork.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Cream the butter and cheese together. Add salt and pepper and mix thoroughly. Add flour and Rice Krispies. Will be stiff.
Pinch and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 18 minutes. Makes about 80.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly butter, sugar and vanilla. Work in flour, salt and nuts until dough holds together.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool and then roll in confectioners sugar again.
Makes several dozen.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in a greased pan or skillet.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add all other ingredients, zucchini last.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (golden brown).

title: spam noodles
directions: Boil wide egg noodles as directed on package. In a skillet, add butter. Dice Spam into little chunks, then brown. Add cream of chicken soup to your noodles with Spam. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients, refrigerate overnight if possible. Serve with crackers.

title: friendship sourdough starter
directions: Mix flour, sugar, yeast and salt in a large bowl.
Gradually stir in water.
Beat or whisk until smooth.
Cover with a towel and set in a warm place.
Stir 2 to 3 times a day or until the starter is bubbly and produces a yeasty aroma.

title: pumpkin tea rings
directions: Mix all together.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Use 2 loaf pans.
This freezes well.

title: barbecue
directions: Saute onions.
Add corned beef and ground beef.
Cook until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour before serving.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Beat oil and eggs lightly.
Add salt and muffin mix.
Mix in creamed corn and sour cream.
Pour into hot greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Make sauce out of first 5 ingredients.
Mix well in blender. Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste. Layer casserole dish with: chips, meat, sauce, cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: colorful cole slaw
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in
a mixing bowl and toss to blend. Cover
and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving to let flavors blend.

title: sour cream shrimp dip
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl.
Blend well.
Add mayonnaise, onion, Worcestershire sauce and parsley.
Break up shrimp with fork.
Stir in sour cream mixture.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Serve on Triscuits.
Yields 3 cups.

title: blender poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process on low speed for 30 seconds.
Cover and chill; stir well before serving.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: shrimp and angel hair pasta
directions: Cook and drain the pasta according to directions. Saute the butter, garlic and tomatoes for 10 minutes over medium heat. Stir in the Ranch dressing and shrimp. Serve over pasta.

title: peanutty chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, peanut butter, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of the batter into a 12 cup microproof Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup each of the peanuts and chips over batter.
Pour another 1/3 of batter over peanuts and chips.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup each of peanuts and chips over batter.
Repeat with remaining batter, peanuts and chips.
Cook on 70% power for 17 to 18 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Invert onto serving platter.
Spoon warm Caramel Glaze over cake and let cool. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all stuff together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with one stack of Ritz crackers crumbled in a frying pan with 1/2 stick butter.
Bake until brown.
Will be more moist if you put a can of mushroom soup in mixture.

title: souper meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion, egg and bread crumbs; add 1/2 cup of soup and 1/2 of the granules.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done. Mix 1/2 cup soup and other half of granules together.
Pour on top.
Put back in oven and bake for 10 minutes.

title: fake fried oysters
directions: Cut mushrooms in half.	Take
the
egg and 1/4 cup milk and mix well in large bowl.
Add mushrooms and cover with more milk. Let set for
minutes.
Mix
well
once.
In another bowl, put about 1 cup
flour	and
salt
and	pepper to taste. Pick up mushrooms with hand
(do
not drain) and mix in flour. Fry	until golden brown.
Tastes like oysters, and the cost is much less.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind and boil for 30 minutes.
When thick, pour into jars and seal.

title: les grives a la broche(spit roasted thrushes)
directions: Six hours before cooking is to begin, pluck, singe, lard and truss the thrushes.
They should not be drawn. Put the birds into a deep dish just big enough to hold them in one layer.
Cover with the white wine, juniper berries, sliced onion, garlic cut in half, thyme and cayenne pepper.

Leave to marinate for 6 hours at room temperature, turning the birds every hour. Toast 6 slices of bread lightly and arrange in a dripping pan so they will catch the cooking juices of the thrushes. Dab the thrushes dry with the kitchen paper.
Smear with olive oil.
Put them on a skewer and grill for 10 to 15 minutes, ideally in front of a blaze of vine branches.
Scoop out the insides of each bird and spread on the pieces of toast.
Put the thrushes on top and serve.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients; add to zucchini mixture and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bread tests done (toothpick comes out clean).

title: bluebell crunch
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in bottom of baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients like crumbs and sprinkle over other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with milk or ice cream.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: In ovenproof skillet, brown chops; pour off fat.
Add salt and pepper.
Top each chop with onion and pepper ring; pour soup over. Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more or until tender.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cracker crumbs.
Heat margarine and peanut butter over low heat until melted; stir to crumb mixture. Press in ungreased baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Heat chocolate chips in small saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently, until melted.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate until firm, about 30 minutes.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 3 dozen candies.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and pumpkin.
Blend sugar, spice, flour and salt. Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell; bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near center comes out clear.
Cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook slowly until thick.
May be doubled or tripled.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Place bread in dish, then cheese and then sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over bread, cheese and sausage.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Put into cold oven. Set oven to 350° and bake 45 minutes.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Peel, dice and keep warm.
Fry bacon crisp, drain and crumble.
Fry onion in drippings.
Mix soup, milk, vinegar and relish.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle top with bacon and eggs.

title: orange soda bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and baking soda in a bowl.
Make a well in the center and pour in buttermilk and orange juice; mix well.
Add egg, raisins and orange peel; beat until smooth (dough will be sticky).
Knead lightly on a well-greased 9-inch round layer cake pan.
Cut an X across the top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp mold deluxe
directions: Chop shrimp, pimento, eggs and celery separately in blender. Place in bowl.
Put gelatin into blender.
Add boiling water. Cover and process on "stir" until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and process on "mix" until smooth.
Pour over mixture in bowl and mix well.
Pour into well-greased 1-quart mold and chill thoroughly.
This mold will stand up, yet is soft enough for dip.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil fryer.
Let cool and take meat off of bones.
Put chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Drain Veg-All and spread vegetables on top of chicken.
Mix soup and broth together and pour over vegetables.
Mix well Bisquick, buttermilk and butter.
Pour on top of casserole to form a crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn on broil to brown top.

title: mexican fried rice
directions: Put bacon grease and rice in frying pan over low heat.
Stir occasionally until lightly brown.
Add onions, cumin, salt, chili powder, tomatoes and water.
Cover with a tight lid and cook over low heat until rice is done.
Add more water if necessary.

title: spanish beans
directions: Soak washed beans in water overnight with 1/4 teaspoon baking soda.
If overnight is impossible, bring beans with water and 1/4 teaspoon baking soda to boil for 2 minutes only.
Cover and allow to stand one hour.
This is equal to 12 to 15 hours soaking. Rinse beans and put in heavy pot with 5 cups water and 1/4 teaspoon soda.
Bring to a boil and add 2 tablespoons bacon grease and salt.
Reduce heat to simmer; cover tightly and cook 2 hours. Cut bacon in 1/4 and fry partially; add to beans with all other ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Better if made a day ahead and reheated.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Mix above and put in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Wash and dry 4 to 6 chicken breasts, salt and pepper and put on top of rice.
Sprinkle 1 envelope Lipton's dry onion soup mix over chicken.
Cover casserole with heavy duty aluminum foil and seal all around.
Bake 2 hours at 325°.
Don't peek.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Beat the eggs, oil and vanilla together in a bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir mixture until just combined.
Fill muffin pans to the brim and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Crush crackers; add melted margarine and press to bottom of pie pan.
Saute onions and put over crust.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and pepper and pour over onions.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate nut sundae cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
When done, while hot, put holes in cake and pour chocolate syrup over cake (save a little). Refrigerate until cold.
Mix vanilla instant pudding as directed. Pour over cake; add Cool Whip over pudding.
Drizzle walnut topping and remainder of chocolate syrup over cake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.
Use as a dip for apple slices which have been dipped in lemon juice or Fruit Fresh to retain color.

title: big cookie
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Grease and flour round 15-inch pan. Spread batter to edges of pan with wax paper and a rolling pin. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix green pepper, pickles, onion and salt in a bowl and let set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Drain; do not rinse.
Add sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Mix with pickles, onion and green pepper.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours, then put in containers and freeze.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Chop onions and green pepper.
Add rest of ingredients to crock-pot.
Slow cook for 3 to 5 hours. Serve.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Put tamales in 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with chili, onions and cheese.
Heat with lid on, 5 to 6 minutes, in microwave.
Serve with corn chips.
Very easy, very fast.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Grease tube pan and coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Leave remaining mix in bottom of pan.
Beat all other ingredients for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients into 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork roast and apples
directions: Combine salt, ginger, nutmeg and cinnamon and rub over roast, saving some for apples.
Place roast fat side up in shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours. During the last half hour, add apples to pan and sprinkle with remaining spice mixture.
Cover roast and let stand for 15 minutes before slicing.

title: easy potato rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add potatoes, salt and eggs.
In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in 2/3 cup warm water; add to creamed mixture.
Beat in 2 cups flour and rest of water.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Shape into a ball; do not knead.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to coat. Cover and let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch down; divide into thirds.
Shape each portion into 15 balls and arrange in 3 greased round baking pans.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until water is absorbed.

title: melba toast
directions: Arrange bread on cookie sheet.
Place in a 325° oven.
Let dry.
Remove after each side has browned.

title: english toffee crunch
directions: Spread dessert topping on bottom of pie crust.
Pour milk in a large bowl; add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk for two minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in the Cool Whip and chopped toffee bars.
Spoon in crust.
Freeze 4 hours.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes or until pie cuts easily.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine green pepper, cabbage, onion and sugar.
Bring to boil vinegar, salt, mustard seed, celery seed and sugar.
Mix all together in glass bowl and add oil.
Let stand 3 hours.
Chill and serve.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Mix all together; add dressing.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cream salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine jello with boiling water and stir for 2 minutes. Stir in cold water and pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Refrigerate approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until firm. In another bowl, combine cream cheese, crushed pineapple, sugar, lemon juice and nuts. Mix together and fold into jello mixture. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and then add the other ingredients
to
this mixture.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: butter sauce
directions: Pour 1/2 cup butter over a layer of gnocchi and sprinkle with 1/3 cup of cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Serve immediately.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Bring sugars and syrup to a boiling point; boil for 1 minute. Add 1 cup peanut butter; stir until blended.
Pour over corn flakes and peanuts.
Mix and press into buttered pan.
Frost with mixture of chocolate chips, 3 tablespoons peanut butter and butter.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: chicken italiano(heart-healthy recipe)
directions: Prepare in an electric skillet

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour, pepper and milk.
Add corn and butter.
Cook at 350° until firm, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: semester muffins
directions: *Flour can be unbleached or wheat blend.

title: jayne's breath of death spaghetti
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add tomato sauce and simmer.
In a bowl, mix seasonings, Ragu and envelope contents.
Put all ingredients, meat mixture and mushrooms into crock-pot and slow cook 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over freshly cooked pasta.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger; remove grease.
Put in casserole dish.
Add green beans, soup and Tater Tots layered on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine all except sour cream.
In clear glass dish, congeal half.
After congealed, spread sour cream over it.
Pour other half of salad over sour cream.
Congeal overnight.

title: ambrosia
directions: Whip heavy cream with Sweet 'N Low packets.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Beat together Gicatta and cream cheese, sugar and cornstarch, then add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and lemon; spoon into pan.
Bake 1 hour; turn oven off.
Leave in oven 30 minutes after turning oven off.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Core a large head of cabbage and place in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Place a handful of mixture in each leaf and roll up and place in baking dish.
Pour a No. 2 can of tomatoes over the top.
Cook, uncovered, in a 450° oven for 30 minutes, then 1 1/2 hours, covered in 380° oven.

title: coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, blend Lipton Soup mix with sour cream, then add cabbage, carrots, pepper, and vinegar and mix well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 qt.

title: open-faced vegetable melt
directions: This meatless sandwich resembles a French bread pizza.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix.
Do not refrigerate.
It is stiff enough dough already. Bake until light brown in a 325° oven (about 8 minutes).

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Steam whole zucchini until they are tender-crisp, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Slice lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices.

title: oven chicken and rice
directions: Mix together all ingredients except chicken and paprika.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Remove foil and bake 10 to 20 minutes more.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: In skillet, saute chopped onion in butter.
Add broccoli, soup, milk and Cheez Whiz.
Add rice; mix well.
Put in casserole and heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly and partly brown.
Don't overcook.

title: company french toast
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan; add sugar and cinnamon. Place 12 slices of bread in a pan (2 slices deep).
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: fire and ice salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers; cut tomatoes into wedges. (If very large, cut wedges in half.) Chop or dice onion medium fine. Dissolve sugar in vinegar and water. Add salt and white pepper to taste. Keeps well for up to a week.

title: 8 layer dip(serves 12)
directions: Place these ingredients in the order given in a pan or dish. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 30 minutes, covered.
Cook spaghetti according to directions on box.
About 10 minutes before serving, mix sauce and spaghetti in one pan and heat.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Put all ingredients (liquid first) into a blender.
Blend for one minutes.
Add nuts if desired after blending.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: To 2 packages of jello, add hot water and stir well.
Add cranberry and drained pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Clean and trim vegetables.
Soak in ice water 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix other ingredients and heat.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: kahlua fruit dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add brown sugar and Kahlua until blended.
Add sour cream.
Fold in nuts.
Chill.

title: swiss carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 2-quart baking dish, combine carrots, soup, half of the swiss cheese and half of the fried onions. Be careful not to mash the carrots. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Sprinkle remaining fried onions on top of cheese. Bake 5 more minutes to melt cheese.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients except Kisses in large mixing bowl. Mix on lowest speed of mixer until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls, using a rounded teaspoon for each.
Roll balls in sugar. Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie immediately with candy Kiss; press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.

title: quick macaroni and cheese dish
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to directions on box.
Cook peas according to directions on package.
Slice and quarter hot dogs.
Add hot dogs to the boiling peas during the last minute of boiling.
Drain.
Add peas and hot dogs to the macaroni and cheese.
Serve.

title: raisin treats
directions: Flatten biscuits with fingers.
Mix cheese with raisins. Place a spoonful in center of each biscuit.
Fold dough up around filling.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a greased dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix sugar and egg; mix well.
Add shortening and apples.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with milk or cream.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine the Soup, Sour Cream and Garlic Salt. Add Potatoes and Cheddar Cheese; mix well.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Top with Parmesan Cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350 for 55 - 60 minutes or until Potatoes are tender. Yield:
12 - 16 servings.

title: grandma's chicken casserole
directions: Mix together stuffing, water and oleo.
Spread 1/2 in buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish, then mix chicken, onions, celery, mayonnaise and salt.
Place in baking dish on top of stuffing mixture, then top with remaining 1/2 of mixture.
Beat eggs and milk and pour over bread mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, apples, celery, walnuts and raisins in a bowl. Toss and mix.
Mix yogurt with honey and drained crushed pineapple.
Stir yogurt mixture into chicken mixture and toss until well coated.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Garnish with seedless white grapes or mandarin oranges.
This is better if eaten the day it is prepared.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl. Add oil and milk all at once to dry mixture.
Mix only until blended.
Do not overmix. Form into a ball. Pat out on lightly floured surface to 3/4-inch thickness. Cut into biscuits with cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 475° for 10 minutes or golden brown.
Yields 10 biscuits.

title: golden turkey enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, chilies and salt. Reserve 3/4 cup sauce and mix the rest with the turkey or chicken and 1/2 cup cheese.
Slightly fry the tortillas in heated oil, one at a time. Fill while still hot with meat mixture.
Roll and place seam side down in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine reserved sauce with milk and pour over tortillas.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and sprinkle with remaining cheese and onions while hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into ball. Roll in chopped pecans.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Brown onions in oil. Add Creole seasoning, garlic, celery seed, bouillon cubes, shrimp and 2 cups of water.
Cook until shrimp is done.
Add parsley and hot sauce, cook for 10 minutes.

title: sicilian soup
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, sugar, broth, basil, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Add pasta.
When it boils turn down heat a bit and cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
If needed, add more broth.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells until tender; rinse and cool so you can handle. Cook meat until brown.
Remove excess oil.
Thaw spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add peanut butter and eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to mixture.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press with floured fork.
Bake at 375°.

title: old virginia coconut pie
directions: Bake in raw pastry shell at 400° for approximately 1 hour. (Cover edges of pie crust with foil to avoid becoming overdone.) Pie is ready when filling is lightly browned on top.

title: cheese surprise
directions: Mix cheese, butter, flour, salt, paprika.
Roll dough and cut into squares.
Wrap dough squares around olives.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
These may be reheated to serve warm.

title: creamed corn
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, pour in milk and cornstarch; mix well.
Add margarine, corn and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: green river
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool to room temperature. Cut 1 lime in half and squeeze both halves into gelatin.
Cut remaining lime into quarters.
Fill 4 tall glasses with crushed ice.
Add 2 tablespoons of gelatin mixture to each glass.
Fill glasses with club soda and stir.
Top with lime wedges and cherries.
Serve.

title: 2 hour buns
directions: Use a good size bowl.
Beat the first 4 ingredients with egg beater until mixture is foaming, then add the salad oil, salt and flour.
Knead enough to blend well.
Let rise until double in size.
Make into buns; let rise again.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in hot oven at 375°.

title: glorified beans
directions: Brown hamburger. Cube bacon and brown.
Discard grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir.
Put in crock-pot on low for several hours or bake in a 350° oven, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pig in a blanket
directions: Mix hamburger, onion (diced), bread (crumbled), egg and raw rice together.
Wrap in raw cabbage leaves.
Place in roaster. Pour tomatoes and tomato sauce on top.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Remove 1 cup cake mix.
Mix remainder of cake mix, 1 stick oleo and 1 egg with fork.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.

title: sweet potatoes casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a quart casserole dish.

title: lazy cook's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together melted butter, barbecue sauce and onion soup mix.
Thoroughly coat chicken with mixture. Cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until the sauce gets "crusty."

title: easy toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch cookie sheet (including sides).
Arrange graham crackers on bottom of pan (some may need to be broken so entire bottom of pan is covered).

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in the shortening.
Mix 1 cup buttermilk and about 3/4 cup water or add some more buttermilk.
Add liquid until of a good consistency.
Turn onto a floured surface and knead until it can be handled good.
Pinch off biscuits; turn in a little oil.
Bake at 450°.
Place leftover dough in covered bowl and place in refrigerator until needed. Will keep 3 or 4 days.
It's better baked the next morning.

title: chicken chili(chili cook off entry - 1994)
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Cook chicken, onion, green pepper and garlic in hot oil in a Dutch oven until lightly browned.
Add other ingredients; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: garden yellow squash salad
directions: Combine squash, green onion, green pepper and celery in large bowl.
Toss lightly.
Combine wine vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, canola oil, cider vinegar and garlic.
Mix well and spoon over vegetables.
Chill about 12 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put melted margarine in bottom of pan.
Swish on sides and bottom.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly on bottom.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top next.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly on top of chips.
Next sprinkle coconut evenly on top.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together in baking dish the vegetables, mayonnaise and onion.
Top that with 3 ounces (save 1 ounce for top) mild Cheddar cheese.
Then spread crackers over that and finish with remainder of the cheese for the topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup.
Stir in nuts.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is settled or set.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Cut up berries and place in shell.
Combine pudding and Jell-O; add water and bring to a boil. Pour over berries and refrigerate.
Takes a good three hours to set.
Also great with peaches using peach Jell-O, or blackberries using blackberry Jell-O.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a buttered casserole dish. Add coconut (optional).

title: crock of barbecue beans
directions: Brown meat and onions in butter.
Mix everything together and put in a crock-pot on low for about 3 hours.

title: honey-mustard pork chops
directions: In small bowl, stir together mustard, oil and honey; set aside.
Place chops on rack of broiler pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat source for 8 minutes.
Brush with half the sauce.
Broil 2 minutes longer.
Turn chops and broil 8 minutes.
Brush with remaining sauce.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes longer or until tender and browned.
Serves 4.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Combine all ingredients except mushrooms and bake in covered casserole dish for 4 to 5 hours at 250°.
Add mushrooms last hour. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
(If batter is too thick, add a little milk.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Thoroughly beat eggs and combine with sugar, butter, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in coconut and pour filling into uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender until smooth. Store jars in refrigerator.
Serve hot or cold on meats.

title: nutty strawberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water.
Fold in the strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Put half of mixture into a dish or mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread the sour cream over the mixture, then spread rest of gelatin mixture over the sour cream (leave the second half at room temperature so will spread easier). Refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Cut 6 tortillas in 1 inch squares and fry in hot oil until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and set aside.
Cut the other tortillas in squares and set aside.

title: s.u.n.y. girl's real buffalo chicken wings
directions: *Frank's Louisiana Hot; I actually use a lot more pepper sauce, but we like them HOT; adjust sauce to your taste.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Note: If using self-rising flour, omit salt and baking powder. If using plain flour, use all ingredients.

title: crab custard casserole
directions: Butter bread on both sides; cut into cubes.
Put first 3 ingredients into well-greased casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over crab combination.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Wash and slice unpeeled potatoes.
Place overlapping slices in buttered oven to table 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix oil and butter.
Brush slices with mixture.
Pour remaining over potatoes. Sprinkle with garlic, salt and thyme.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are done and browned at the edges.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease loaf pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
In another bowl, combine eggs, brown sugar and oil.
Mix with electric mixer on medium until creamy.
Stir in sweet potatoes until well combined.
Add dry mixture to wet mixture half at a time.
Mix until blended completely.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: french green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add salt, pepper, flour and sour cream.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add drained green beans; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Chill for 30 minutes. Roll out
on
floured
board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: sweet relish
directions: Let the cucumbers or zucchini, onions and bell peppers soak with the salt for 30 minutes.
Combine the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, then add drained relish (the first 4 ingredients).
Let boil for 5 minutes.
Can and seal while hot.

title: squash patties
directions: Mix together and fry in hot skillet with a little vegetable oil (pancake style).

title: freezer slaw
directions: Chop bell pepper, cabbage and carrot fine.
Boil together the celery seed, mustard seed, vinegar and sugar; pour over vegetable mixture.
Stir well; let stand for 2 hours.
Put in freezer containers; leave in freezer until ready to use.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix in order given; stir and simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: kookie kat sundae
directions: Using instant chocolate icing, "glue" 3/4 of a round chocolate waver onto a chocolate covered marshmallow cookie.
This makes the fan tail.
Next, glue a candy corn to the opposite side, making the head.
Easy to make and kids have fun with them!

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: janice's carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, and then add oil.
Beat approximately two minutes.
Add eggs, beat two minutes.
Stir in carrots, mixing thoroughly and then add nuts.
Pour in Bundt pan sprayed heavily with Butter Pam.
Bake at 325° for approximately 60-70 minutes or until done.

title: chocaroon pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 inch pie pan. Combine milk and coconut, spoon over chocolate mixture, leaving a 1/2 inch to 1 inch border.	Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour and nutmeg.
Cut steak in small cubes, dust with flour.
Brown in small amount of oil.
Add the water, bouillon cubes and onion soup.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours over low heat. Stir from time to time.
Cook noodles according to directions; drain.
Combine noodles, sour cream and meat mixture.

title: four tier delight
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chili tamale casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni in 6 cups boiling water (salted) until tender (10 to 12 minutes); drain.
Cook ground beef in 10-inch skillet until light brown; drain.
Stir in macaroni, sauce mix, corn (with liquid), water and chili powder.
Pour into ungreased baking dish (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch).
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Top with lettuce, onion and cheese.
Makes 5 servings.

title: low-fat mashed potatoes
directions: Put potatoes into a large pan with the milk, water, bay leaf, onion and peppercorns. Add enough additional water to cover the potatoes by 1-inch. Bring the liquid to a boil, lower the heat and let the liquid bubble steadily for 20 minutes or until the potatoes are very tender and almost falling apart.

Lift the potatoes from the cooking water (discard the bay leaf, onion and peppercorns) and transfer them to a bowl. Do not discard cooking water. Add 2 tablespoons of the cooking liquid to mash the potatoes with a potato masher or a pastry blender until they are blended with the liquid.
Add 2 more tablespoons of the water until the potatoes are light and fluffy. Add another tablespoon if necessary. Beat in the butter, salt and pepper and serve at once. Serves 6.

title: black-eyed texan casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain. Blend all ingredients in casserole and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until cheese is bubbly. Serve with cornbread.
You have
a complete meal.
Great for leftover peas and rice.

title: minister's pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat white sugar into egg whites.
Crumble Ritz crackers and add to egg whites.
Add walnuts to mixture.
Pat into pie tin.
Bake 25 minutes at 325° to 350°. Cool.
Add Cool Whip and spread over cooked pie.
(Can add 1/2 teaspoon coffee to Cool Whip for mocha flavor.)

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped pecans.
Flatten in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.
Let cool.
Combine confectioners sugar and cream cheese; spread on crust.
Mix pudding and milk; congeal in refrigerator.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: blt dip
directions: Cook and drain bacon.
It is easier to crumble if it is really crispy.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, and ranch dressing. Crumble in bacon.
Chill for an hour.
Seed and cut up tomatoes. Add tomatoes just before serving.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Toss vegetables and eggs together.
Chill. Before serving, toss with Classic Garlic Dressing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Fry livers with onions in butter until onions are tender and livers are cooked.
Chop livers and onions very finely and add a little mayonnaise to mix together.
Serve on crackers.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Top with crushed pineapple.
Use your favorite yellow cake mix. Follow box directions.
Use pineapple juice as part of the liquid in cake.
Bake according to box directions.
When done, flip cake out on tray.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, grated onion, celery seed, sugar, salt and pepper.
Drain the cabbage thoroughly and mix with the dressing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pound cake made healthy
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating 4 minutes or until well blended.
Add vanilla and almond. Beat at low speed until well blended.
Set aside.
Combine flour, soda and salt. Add alternately with yogurt to creamed mixture. Use flour first and last.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake 65 minutes at 350°.
Contains 150 calories per 1/2-inch slice.
No cholesterol.

title: easy penuche icing
directions: Melt margarine and stir in brown sugar.
Cook until bubbly. Remove from heat.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Add confectioners sugar until desired consistency.

title: upside-down apple-pecan pie
directions: In 9 or 10-inch pie plate, spread the combined sugar and butter in bottom of plate.
Place pecans over sugar mixture and press in.
Now, place 1 pastry circle over sugar mixture, leaving the edge hanging over.

title: spinach ranch roll-ups
directions: In food processor, mix cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and package of dressing. Process until thoroughly mixed and creamy. Transfer to medium size bowl. Then add remaining ingredients, except tortillas. Mix well. Spread enough mixture on a tortilla to cover. Roll up in foil. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Remove foil. Slice (about 1/2-inch thick) and serve on small platter. You can also freeze these and thaw 2 hours before serving. Enjoy.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix above ingredients and pour into greased skillet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: sour creamed green beans
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup margarine.
Add to combined beans, sour cream, flour and seasonings; mix lightly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with crumbs, tossed with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix together peanut butter, margarine and sugar.
Knead mixture like bread dough.
Form mixture into balls, buckeye size. Place the balls on a tray lined with wax paper.
Stick a toothpick in each ball.
Chill.

title: oatmeal coconut crispies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, blending well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and oats. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire rack immediately.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: pie crust (2)
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in Tupperware Thatsa Bowl or Fix-N-Mix bowl; shake and burp.
(Add small portions of Crisco at a time for best results.)
Add the ice water.
Shake until it forms a ball and thumps.
Yields 2 delicious flaky crusts!

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Put in casserole dish. In a bowl, mix tuna, soups, mushrooms, onion, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Add milk gradually to thicken as you stir.
Pour over noodles and mix well.
Crumble bread finely and put into enough melted butter or margarine to soak them lightly.
Put crumbs over top of casserole.
Put in a 350° oven and bake for 30 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: company potato casserole
directions: Mix together sour cream, chicken soup and onion. Put layer of thinly sliced potatoes in bottom of large casserole dish. Spread with some of the sour cream mixture. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and a layer of cheese. Repeat layers until all is used. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, water and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; cook until all berries have popped.
Remove from heat. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple and nuts. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch glass pan or your favorite mold; chill until firm.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart pan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Press this into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels together.
Spread over contents in pan.
Cool and cut.

title: sprouts for dinnerdallas, texas
directions: Stir fry 8 oz. of sprouts for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: easy barbecue sauce for cooked meat
directions: If fresh onion is used, brown in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and approximately 2 cups cut up meat (chicken, turkey, beef or pork).
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch pecan pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Gradually add flour, mixing at lowest speed just until blended after each addition. Stir in flavorings, pecans and morsels.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on a wire rack.
Yield:
one 10-inch cake.

title: chicken and rice dinner
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir in rice and soup.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange chicken over rice mixture.
Pour water over top; sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed.
Cool.
Lightly squeeze all water out of spinach.
Mix all ingredients and form balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
These freeze nicely.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat milk and pudding.
Mix on low for 2 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fold in half of the whipped cream.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze for 5 minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Garnish with remaining whipped cream and chocolate bar.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells according to directions on box.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain excess fat.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Let the bread touch.
Layer meat and cheese.
Cover with another layer of bread squares.
Mix eggs with butter, milk and salt; pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp sauce piquant
directions: In iron pot, heat cooking oil.
Add onion, garlic, celery and pepper and fry until transparent.
Add tomato sauce and other seasoning.
Simmer and stir for about 1 hour, then add shrimp and let simmer 1 hour longer.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa and milk in a pan; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter, oats and pecans (if desired). Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: In large, heavy saucepan, melt butter, sugar, syrups and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Slowly pour over popcorn and nuts mixing well.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven and cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
In a baking dish, put 1/2 macaroni and 1/2 cheese.
Add margarine and salt.
Add other 1/2 macaroni and cheese.
Add milk and water.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
This is delicious!

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: In
mixing
bowl,
blend
cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Beat until blended.
Stir in dry jello.
Fold in pineapple and oranges. Keep refrigerated.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt
in a microwave bowl.
Cook 6 to 9 minutes (until peanuts are light brown).
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes longer.
Quickly stir in baking soda until mixture is foamy.
While foamy, pour onto greased cookie sheet to cool.
You need to work fast to be able to spread mixture out thin.

title: homemade pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine sugar and salt with milk; stir into yeast.
Beat 1 cup flour into dough until smooth.
Add remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Cut dough into 2 pieces.
Pour 1 tablespoon oil onto pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Spread oil with fingers, then pat 1 piece of dough into pizza shape.
(Start in middle of dough and work out to edge.)
Repeat with second piece of dough.

title: chicken breasts cacciatore
directions: Brown breasts in a large nonstick skillet: arrange in single layer in an 8 cup shallow casserole. Top each breast with an onion slice.

title: turkey fajitas
directions: In a 1-quart bowl, combine turkey, cilantro, garlic, cumin, chili powder, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add egg, milk and melted shortening; beat well and pour into well-greased
muffin tins (until half full).
This recipe makes 12.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Layer tomatoes alternately with sugar in a large mixing bowl; sprinkle
with
citrus
rind
and
juice.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 8 hours.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken.
Crumble bread in large mixing bowl.
Add boiling broth.
Cover and let set 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Pour in greased baking dish and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Serve with chicken and giblet gravy.

title: joyce clark's 24 hour lettuce-pea salad
directions: Cook peas and let cool. Cut lettuce head up into large bowl. Add a layer of green pepper, celery and onions. After peas have cooled, add a layer of peas over the
onions.
Spread mayonnaise layer. Sprinkle the sugar over the mayonnaise.
Add cheese layer and then bacon layer.
Stir before serving.

title: cranberry-hazelnut stuffing
directions: In small saucepan, bring cranberries and orange juice to boiling.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In a large skillet, cook celery and onion in hot margarine until tender.
Stir in poultry seasoning; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine stuffing mix, apple, cooked sausage, rice, nuts and parsley.
Stir in cranberry mixture, celery and onion mixture.
Drizzle with enough chicken broth to moisten, tossing lightly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Use to stuff an 8 to 10 pound turkey or bake in an uncovered, ungreased 3-quart casserole at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sun pickles
directions: Mix vinegar and water; pour in salt and mix until salt is dissolved.
Pack pickles, garlic and dill (can be fresh) in gallon jar.
Pour liquid mixture over pickles.
Place in sun for 2 days, then eat or refrigerate.

title: ham casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
Add cheese and milk.
Stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Heat well, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Refrigerate before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cookie sheet chocolate chips
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: sandra's cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add yolks and flour.
Refrigerate until firm.
Then form into small balls; roll in slightly beaten egg whites, then in nuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press a piece of candied cherry on top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields approximately 55.

title: german pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well with eggbeater or mixer.
Heat flat, well seasoned griddle over medium-high heat.
Pour about 1 soup ladle full of batter onto hot griddle.
Run batter over entire surface of griddle by carefully tipping griddle.
When pancake surface is shiny, carefully lift to check for doneness and flip with a large turner.
Done when lightly browned on both sides. Serve with warmed syrup or powdered sugar and lemon wedges. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mors tebrod
directions: Cream 1 cup of sugar and butter together.
Mix second cup of sugar with the eggs and then beat with the butter mixture.
Add flour and baking powder to this mixture and mix well.
Divide dough into 6 parts (the size of a child's wrist; 6 rolls of dough).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until light brown. Remove, and when easy to handle, cut into slices 1/2-inch thick. Spread out on cookie sheet and dry in the oven at 300°.
Turn over after about 10 minutes and dry 10 more minutes on the other side or until brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms.
Put in pan.
Add vinegar, salt and boil 10 minutes.
Drain and add oil and seasoning.
Refrigerate.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Scald the milk and put butter in it.
Then put sugar and salt in bowl.
Soften yeast in water.
Pour milk over sugar and salt and cool.
Add yeast, beaten eggs and flour.
Let rise.
Roll out and put a combination of butter, brown sugar, cinnamon, nuts and cherries inside.
Roll up and let rise again.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan while oven is preheating to 425°.
Remove and set aside.
In plastic bag, mix well the remaining ingredients except chicken.
Add chicken, 2 pieces at a time, and shake until well coated.
Place chicken in pan skin side down.
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn and bake another 15 to 20 minutes, or until it is fork-tender.

title: confederate coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add milk and unbeaten egg.
Mix well. Sift the flour and baking powder; blend with the sugar and butter, adding nutmeg, cinnamon, nuts and granulated sugar.
Dot well with butter and bake in a moderate, about 320°, for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and butter; mix thoroughly. Spread evenly in a 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then put on frosting.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas.
Spread on tortillas, roll up and cut into slices.
Dip in salsa.

title: baked garlic for 4
