directions: Peel loose skins off garlic bunch, slice top to a flat surface. Drizzle with olive oil; mound basil paste onto bunch.
Place on baking sheet, in 400° oven for approximately 40 minutes or until soft, with fork.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly; add milk.
Mix sugar and flour together.
Stir into egg mixture.
Blend in syrup.
Combine cocoa with enough water to make thin paste.
Stir into egg mixture.
Add butter.
Cook in double boiler or microwave until thick, stirring frequently.
Pour into shell.

title: casserole of peas
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir breadcrumbs with butter and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rotel chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts with 1/2 cup of the diced onions.
When chicken is done, remove from broth.
Save broth.
Remove skin and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Add more water to broth in order to cook spaghetti.
Meanwhile, mix remaining onion, Ro-Tel tomatoes, soup, bell pepper and Velveeta.
Heat mixture on low heat until cheese melts. Do not allow to burn or stick to pot. When spaghetti has cooked, drain water off and stir spaghetti into the tomato mixture.
Pour into a lightly greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix all of the above together.
Let set over night.
Next morning knead lightly, put in muffin pan and let rise 4 to 6 hours.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes.

title: rum lime sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, mix sugar and water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Add grated lime rind.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in lime juice and rum.

title: peanut surprises cookies
directions: Cream shortening and add rest of ingredients in order given. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a moderate 400° oven.

title: apple pie
directions: Toss the apples in a mixture of the sugar and spices and fold into the pie crust.
Top with a mixture of butter, flour and brown sugar.
Place the pie in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Then reduce the heat to 325° and bake for another 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix together sugar and hot water.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add coconut extract.
Mix well.
Punch holes in the hot cake and pour mixture over cake.
Let the cake cool for 1 hour before removing from pan.
May sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired, after removing from pam.

title: squash casserole 5
directions: Mash squash and onion and place in rectangular casserole.
Mix broken crackers and soup and pour over squash mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Put in cold oven and turn heat to 350°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until cheese is brown.
Serves 8.

title: sour cream bisquick biscuits
directions: Mix well, bake at 425 degrees until brown.
Makes 36 mini muffin biscuits.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put sliced, cooked sweet potatoes into casserole dish; add salt, milk and 1/2 cup margarine. In a separate bowl, mix the brown sugar, nuts, flour, cinnamon and 1/4 cup unmelted margarine with a fork until crumbly. Put on top of sweet potatoes; spread evenly. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: baked stuffed flounder(lo-cal)
directions: Combine shrimp and stuffing.
Add enough chicken bouillon and water to moisten; stuff flounder.
Wrap in aluminum foil; double fold to seal in moisture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: delightful mayonnaise
directions: Chill oil and juice.
Beat egg well in mixer or blender.
While continuing to beat, slowly add oil using a thin, slow stream.
Beat in salt, sugar and lemon juice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix ingredients and let refrigerate overnight.
Serve with pumpernickel bread or Town House crackers.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Cook the macaroni according to the package directions. Drain and rinse with cold water. Add vinegar, mix lightly and let stand 10 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: *Measure the tomatoes after they are peeled and chopped and juice and seeds have been removed.

title: stir-fried chicken and broccoli
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook chicken, a few pieces at a time, until lightly browned.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add broccoli, pepper, onion and garlic; cook until tender-crisp.
In small bowl, stir together juice, cornstarch, soy sauce, brown sugar and ginger.
Stir into vegetables.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened.
Add reserved chicken pieces and heat through.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 for 15 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Mix together; put cinnamon and cloves in a net into mixture. Bring to a boil, then let simmer.

title: pizzelles (vanilla)
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually and beat until smooth. Add cooled butter and flavoring. Sift flour and baking powder and add to egg mixture. Mix well. (Dough will be sticky.) Bake in pizzelle iron 30 to 35 seconds.

title: cider snap
directions: In 4 cup measure, combine apple cider and cinnamon candies. Microcook, uncovered, on 100% power for 4 to 5 minutes or until candies dissolve and the cider is steaming hot, stirring once. Serve in mugs.
Garnish with apple slices, if desired.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk; let set 15 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites to froth.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff and slowly add sugar until dissolved.
Fold in walnuts. Butter or grease pie plate and pour in meringue.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash, chop and drain strawberries.
Mash two cups of berries and strain to make 1 1/2 cups juice (water may be added if berries do not make quite enough).
Combine sugar and cornstarch and stir into juice.
Bring this to a full boil over medium heat, stirring all of the time.
Boil about 2 minutes.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese by adding cream or milk and spread over bottom of pastry shell.
Put remaining two cups of berries over cheese.
Pour cooled juice mixture of berries and chill for about 2 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: baked vidalia onions(microwave)
directions: Peel onions.
Core and remove a section approximately the diameter of a quarter.
Do not cut through to the bottom.
Fill cavity with 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Place onions in 9-inch glass pie plate.
Cover with plastic wrap, turning back one edge to vent.
Microwave at High (100%) 9 to 11 minutes or until onions are fork-tender.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook peas and carrots.
Drain and set aside.
In large saucepan, add cream of chicken soup and milk.
Allow to simmer until smooth, then add chicken, peas and carrots.
Stir until completely heated.

title: navaho fry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; blend well.
Add water; knead 5 minutes or until the dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover and let stand for 10 minutes.
Pinch off a small amount of dough; roll out like a pancake, 1/16 inch thick.
Fry in hot oil; prick air bubbles.
Fry on each side until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter or honey.

title: kourambiethes
directions: Beat butter until light; add yolks and sugar.
Beat well.
Add chopped nuts and blend in flour and baking powder and mix well. Take a small amount of dough and shape into a half moon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove and roll in powdered sugar.
Cool 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain it.
Add the other ingredients.
Dot casserole with Ritz cracker crumbs and butter. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, combine sugar and cocoa until mixed and melted (or liquefied).
Add butter and work (mix) well. Add cup of milk.
Raise heat to boiling and boil slowly for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and mix in.
Keeps well for at least 1 week in refrigerator.
May be warmed up in microwave.
Serve over ice cream, cake, cream puffs, etc.

title: cheese cake
directions: Use a round 9-inch spring-form pan.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff.
Gradually blend in 1 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Then mix cream cheese with 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Mix this with egg whites and blend.
Pour into pan that you have prepared a graham cracker crust.
You can put cherry filling on crust, if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all together ane bake in greased casserole dish at 250° for 1 hour.

title: rosemary roast chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine parsley, rosemary, lemon pepper and garlic powder.
Crush slightly.
Rinse chicken.
Pat dry.
Brush chicken with oil.
Rub the rosemary mixture onto the skin of chicken.
Place chicken, breast side up, on convection roasting rack.
Set on top of broiler pan.
Convection cook in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans or parsley flakes, and form into a ball.
(Optional:
Roll in pecans or parsley flakes.) Chill and serve.

title: angel food dessert(low-fat)
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Split cake into 2 layers. Frost between layers, top and sides of cake.

title: rusty's peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark in a double boiler.
Add chocolate chips and melt. Add peanuts. Mix well and drop on aluminum foil or wax paper to harden.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows in saucepan.
Add food coloring. Stir in corn flakes.
Drop on wax paper and make into Christmas wreaths.
Decorate with red cinnamon candies.
Very pretty.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Use small bits of onions, mushrooms, bell pepper pieces, bits of celery, an Irish potato leftover or any other veggies, rice, etc.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Work shortening until soft.
Add sugar; work until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Beat eggs; add to shortening mixture.
Mix in flour mixture oats, nuts and coconut thoroughly. (May need to work with hands.)
Roll into size of a walnut, place onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Grease hands with butter or shortening.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: gourmet potatoes casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool, pare and shred coarsely.
In saucepan, over low heat, melt butter and grated cheese, then remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream, salt, pepper and onions. Gently fold in potatoes and pour into greased 3-quart casserole. Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: spaghetti sauce(diabetic meal)
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper; drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken in foil in a 350° oven.
Debone chicken. Save juice from chicken to thin soup with. Add seasonings, onions and chiles to soup.
Dip tortillas in oil just to soften. Drain well. Grease bottom of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and line with 2 tortillas, cut in quarters.
Layer chicken, cut in bite sizes, soup and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven 35 to 45 minutes until briskly bubbling around edges.
Serves 8. Serve with red beans and crisp salad.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Mix together dressing, jam and soup mix.
Using a 9 x 13-inch lightly oiled pan, place chicken pieces.
Cover with sauce and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn to 425° for last 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and margarine; blend well.
Add chips and mold into a ball; refrigerate.
This can be made several days before serving.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain well and rinse off sauerkraut.
Then mix sugar, vinegar, oil and all other ingredients together.
Mix gently.
Store overnight or for 24 hours.
Serves 8 to 12, depending on serving size.
This salad keeps indefinitely in the refrigerator!

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Debone meat. Place in greased casserole dish. Cover with undiluted soup and mix remaining ingredients together. Pour over top of chicken and bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 300° or until top is brown, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut pudding cake
directions: Mix 3/4 cup nuts, flour and butter.
Press into 8 x 12-inch dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cream peanut butter with cream cheese.
Add sugar and mix well.
Fold in 4 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Spread on previous layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and decorate with remaining nuts.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Delicious!

title: strawberry banana milkshake
directions: Place in blender until smooth.
Serve immediately.

title: cashew crunch cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and cream of tartar. Cream together butter and gradually add brown sugar and white sugar; cream well. Blend in egg and vanilla; beat well. Add the dry ingredients gradually and mix thoroughly. Stir in nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 5 dozen.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Saut onion in margarine. Stir in rest of the ingredients and bake in ovenproof dish at 300° for 3 hours or cook in crock-pot until ready to serve.

title: hash brown hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with additional cheese, green pepper or paprika, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.

Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling racks. Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended. Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.

Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake one baking sheet at a time at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies. Do not overbake. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet. Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Wash and drain all vegetables.
Remove stem from peppers and tomatoes.
Core cabbage.
Grind vegetables in a food grinder.
Add salt.
Mix well and let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.

title: eclair cake
directions: Icing:
Boil cocoa, sugar and 1/2 cup milk for 1 minute.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until both are melted.
Set aside.

title: christmas salad
directions: Boil applesauce in saucepan. Stir in small jello. Mix well. Add crushed pineapple and chopped nuts. Mix well. Pour in jello mold. Chill.

title: swedish pie dough
directions: With blender or pastry cutter, mix lard, flour, sugar and salt to crumble stage.
Add slightly beaten egg and milk.
Mix well. This is an easy crust to handle and can be rerolled without toughening.
Extra can be made into pie crusts and frozen or covered and kept in the refrigerator for about 2 weeks.
Yield: 3 double crusts.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all together in blender or food processor.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up jelly roll fashion.
Chill for about 2 hours. Slice into 1-inch pieces.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Dear Patricia:
This prayer has been around since the invention of the three-way mirror, and here it is:

title: tuna casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as on package; drain.
Mix noodles, tuna, mushrooms, sour cream and milk in ungreased casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and butter in separate dish.
Spread over tuna and noodle mixture.
Bake uncovered about 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Mix all ingredients together well. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, mustard, pepper and salt.
Shred both cheeses.
Mince onion, green pepper, pimentos and celery.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: breakfast turkey sausage
directions: Soak oats in V-8 juice for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Shape into logs and freeze just to the solid stage, then slice and store (in patties) in freezer. Patties may be shaped by hand and frozen separately for easy usage.
Cook in a skillet as patties gently thaw during cooking.

title: onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and
1/2 cup butter for crust.
Press into Pyrex dish.
Saute onions and 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour into baking dish. Scald milk and slowly add to beaten eggs. Add cheese and stir until it melts.
Pour mixture into crust and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Wash seeds in a basin, removing all pumpkin fiber.
Boil seeds in salted water for about 5 minutes.
Drain, dry and put in bowl. Coat lightly with oil.
Spread on baking sheet. Toast in slow (250 to 300°) oven, stirring often so seeds do not burn.
When seeds are dry and crisp (about 30 minutes), they are ready to eat.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute onions and okra in oleo for about 10 minutes, stirring to sear okra.
Add tomato and saute 5 minutes.
Add soup stock or broth and green pepper, thyme, bay leaves and shrimp.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: sean's fabulous potato chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat sugar, butter, egg yolk and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Lightly spoon flour into cup; level off.
Add flour to sugar mixture; mix well.
Stir in potato chips and nuts.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and line with graham crackers.
Make pudding using 3 cups of milk.
Mix Cool Whip in with pudding after you have mixed the pudding with milk.
Pour half over graham crackers, layer with more graham crackers, then the rest of the pudding.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Top with Chocolate Icing made as follows.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar, molasses and egg until light and fluffy. Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix with molasses mixture. Drop by teaspoon into the 1/4 cup sugar.
Form into balls.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Balls will flatten and crinkle.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and egg yolk.
Add vanilla, salt and flour.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325°.
Then, melt chocolate chips on top and spread with spatula.
Add nuts (optional).
Bake until just done, lightly brown.

title: peppers stuffed with vegetables and rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Boil enough water to cover peppers in large saucepan.
Add peppers.
Boil 4 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Melt butter flavor Crisco or butter in small skillet on medium heat.
Add onions and celery.
Saute until crisp-tender. Transfer to mixing bowl.
Stir in rice, tomato, chili powder, and salt.
Fill pepper halves generously with rice mixture.
Place in ungreased 9 inch square pan.
Spoon ketchup over top of each filled pepper.
Top each with 2 cheese slices.
Pour water into bottom of pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy sweet potato cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, eggs, sugar, sweet potato, cinnamon and water.
Mix well and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: zucchini-carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In a large bowl, whisk together honey, oil, egg and vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together the flours, oat bran, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add dry ingredients to honey mixture with zucchini, carrots and orange peel.
Stir to blend well.
Add walnuts (if desired).
Spoon into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on a wire rack.
Makes 16 servings (each a 1/2-inch slice).

title: baked navy beans(slow cooker)
directions: Cook dry beans in water until softened, 3 times the volume of water to beans, about 30 minutes.
Let stand for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until softened.
Drain and put in crock-pot with all ingredients well mixed.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours (high 4 to 6 hours), stirring occasionally.

title: cocoa bars(easy)
directions: Cream butter to soften.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla; cream well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in milk.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Add nuts. Spread in a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.
At once, frost cake with Cocoa Frosting.

title: creamy chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Microwave onion, garlic and oil in 2-quart dish on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken, chilies, broth and seasoning. Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add cream cheese; stir until melted. Spoon 1/3 cup chicken mixture into each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in 8-inch square dish.
Microwave Velveeta, milk and 1/4 cup tomato on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir after each minute.
Pour sauce over tortillas; top with remaining tomatoes.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Turn after 3 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: teaberry tapioca
directions: Beat egg white until foamy; gradually beat in half the sugar and continue beating until mixture forms soft rounded peaks.
Mix tapioca, remaining sugar, milk, egg yolk and teaberry candies in a saucepan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook and stir tapioca mixture over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil (pudding thickens more as it cools.) Gradually add to egg white mixture, stirring quickly, until just blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool 20 minutes.
Stir.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bread dip
directions: Mix together.
It is better if it sits overnight in the refrigerator.

title: sausage loaf
directions: Brown sausages together and drain grease.
Lay rolls out to make about 15 x 15-inch square.
Pinch the creases and roll out. (Cut a
little extra dough off for patching.) Add beaten eggs to sausage and spread on flat crescents.
Spread 1 cup shredded Swiss cheese over sausage.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, basil, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Roll up like a jelly roll and patch with extra dough or the mixture will pop out.
(If desired, brush on a beaten egg for a shiny appearance.)
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Layer ingredients.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn in air popper.
Place into brown paper bag.
In large bowl mix corn syrup, brown sugar, salt and melted butter.
Cook in microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir once.
Add soda and vanilla; stir well.
Pour caramel over popcorn and mix with a long wooden spoon.
Fold top of bag over place in microwave.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes on High.
Pour onto large sheet pan and cool.
Store in airtight container if there is any left.

title: tangy shrimp salad
directions: Arrange shrimp on bed of lettuce.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chilled shrimp.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: butter frosting(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine milk and flour in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until a thick sauce results.
Cool completely.
Combine butter, sugar replacement and vanilla in a mixing bowl, beating until fluffy.
Add sauce mixture; beat until consistency of whipped cream.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water, sugar and all but 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Fill peppers.
Arrange in baking dish.
Mix the water, sugar and 1/2 cup tomato sauce; pour over peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° until done.

title: dilly bread
directions: Combine all
ingredients, except softened dry yeast, in a large bowl.
Add
water and yeast mixture.	Stir in 4 1/2 to 5 cups water to
make stiff dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Stir dough down.
Put into 2 well greased casseroles; shape
and
let
rise again.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When done, brush with butter.

title: caramel-nut sticky buns
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients until well mixed; cool.
Spread on 2 or more 8 x 10-inch baking pans.
Add nuts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add shortening, sugar, beaten eggs, salt and flour; mix well.
Mix buttermilk and soda together and add to mixture, then add chopped pecans last.
Bake in buttered and floured loaf pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan or wire rack before cutting.
Wrap tightly.
Will freeze well.

title: "french" coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add tomato sauce; mix well.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Mix garlic clove with cream cheese and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Layer alternately with cooked noodles in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: molasses christmas cookies
directions: Heat molasses to boiling in saucepan deep enough for mixing dough.
Remove from heat.
Stir in shortening and baking soda. Sift in flour, baking powder and spices.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll out dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Decorate with ornamental frosting.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: microwave chicken a la king
directions: Cut boneless chicken into 1/2-inch cubes.
In a dish, combine soup, milk, peas, pimento and chives.
In a colander toss together chicken, mushrooms and broccoli.
Place colander in a dish.
Cover and cook on 100% power (High) for 6 to 8 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and broccoli is tender.
Stir chicken mixture once.
Stir chicken mixture into soup mixture.
Spoon over toasted muffins.
Serves 2.

title: golden asparagus puffs
directions: Place bread on a lightly oiled baking sheet.
Top with tomatoes, cheese and asparagus spears.
Beat egg yolks well, then mix in salt, pepper and dressing.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Spoon egg mixture over asparagus.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until topping is lightly browned.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Mix Parmesan, oil, vinegar, mayonnaise, garlic, onion and salt.
Stir in pasta. Add remaining ingredients and serve.

title: make ahead irish potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water about 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain potatoes and mash.

title: layered green salad
directions: In rectangle glass dish, spread lettuce.
Add peas, cauliflower, onion, pepper, eggs and bacon.
In small bowl, mix mayo, sugar and cheese.
Spread evenly over salad; cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: collard greens
directions: Wash greens well, chop.
In saucepan place greens and chicken broth and cook over medium heat until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Stir sugar and berries up, let stand; bring to a boil Sure-Jell and water, boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, and stir into berry mixture.
Stir 3 minutes.
Pour into medium glasses jar, seal tightly, let stand at room temperature 24 hours. Place in freezer.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients and press into 8x8x2 inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: fake heath bars
directions: Separate graham crackers and place on cookie sheet.
In a saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter and oleo.
Add sugar and bring to a hard boil.
Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: easy, quick, delicious soup
directions: Pour chicken broth into saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add 3/4 of bag of tortellini (frozen) to boiling broth.
Simmer for about 7 to 8 minutes.
Serve in soup bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. I also add 1/2 teaspoon or so of poultry seasoning to broth while it is cooking.

title: skinny dips
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Scoop out most of potato. Sprinkle cheese, bacon and green onion over skins.
Heat in oven at 350° for 4 to 5 minutes, until cheese is bubbly.
Serve with dressing.
Serves 4.

title: garlic green beans
directions: Combine and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: egg custard with fruit(pie)
directions: Mix together all ingredients except fruit and pie shell.
Put fruit in unbaked pie shell.
Pour mixture over fruit and bake at 300° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bruschette(italian appetizer)
directions: Mix together tomatoes, onion, garlic, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Mix well and refrigerate (covered) at least overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and boil until tender. Drain, then mash. Add all ingredients except 1/2 of the margarine to squash.
Melt remaining margarine.
Put squash into baking dish.
Pour remaining margarine over squash and sprinkle with additional cracker meal.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: *Use all, any or none of the three. Personally, the water chestnuts are a must.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda, then add oats.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: see's fudge
directions: Combine butter, vanilla, chips, marshmallow cream and walnuts in a bowl.
Cook sugar and Pet milk for 8 minutes.
Bring to a boil.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: First, leave cream cheese out long enough to soften.
Then, cover one slice of ham with a thick coat of cream cheese.
Take one of the pickles and roll the pickle up in the ham and cream cheese.
Then do the same until all ingredients are used up.
Then place them in the freezer for about 15 minutes.
Take them out and slice them up into desired width.
Arrange on tray and serve.

title: jello fluff
directions: Let set a little.
Whip 2 packages Dream Whip and fold Jell-O mixture into it.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and refrigerate.

title: aloha sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in their jackets until tender, about 25 mins.
Let cool, then peel and cut into slices 1 1/2 inch thick. In a large skillet melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar and water and cook on med. heat about 5 min.
Reduce heat and add sweet potatoes to skillet.
Cook gently; tossing lightly until sweet potatoes are glazed.
Sprinkle with coconut before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: italian seasoning dip
directions: Use 3 tablespoons of each envelope.
Mix all together.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix salt, vinegar, pepper, water and salad oil and bring to a boil; cool.
Drain green beans, peas and corn.
Add pimento, green pepper, celery and onion.
Pour cooled liquid over vegetables. Cool 2 hours before serving.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: chuckles cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs together.
Add soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Fold in oatmeal and coconut.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: better than scratch red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix and cocoa.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, food coloring, margarine and eggs.
Blend until moistened.
Mix soda and vinegar and mix into cake mix.
Beat four minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 325° in layers for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise and soups together.
In buttered casserole, place broccoli on bottom.
Put chicken on top of broccoli.
Spread soup mix over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, taco mix, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Line bottom of 9 x 13 dish with 1/2 tortillas.
Place 1/2 mixture on top and then layer other tortillas and other 1/2 of mixture.
Add can of soup on top of this, then milk and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef marinade(steaks, flank steak, tips, hamburgers)
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Marinate meat at least 2 hours.
Cook as desired.
Baste with remaining marinade.

title: quick barbecue beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together, saving some crumbled bacon for top.
Bake in Pyrex loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses together.
Form in ball and cover with chopped onions.
Also can be used as a dip with vegetables.
Serve with crackers.

title: waldorf salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, toss chopped apples or pears with lemon juice.
Stir in nuts, celery, cherries or raisins and grapes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well. Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Roll breasts in flour.
Heat oil in skillet and brown chicken breasts.
Heat first 7 ingredients.
Place chicken breasts in a casserole dish and top with heated mixture.
Top with pineapple and green pepper slices, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: janice's taco dip
directions: Mix together and spread in the bottom of dish.
Add the following in layers: taco sauce, cheese, lettuce, tomato, onion and black olives.
Refrigerate.

title: almond eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Halve eggplants lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp.
Chop pulp and set aside.
In large skillet heat 1 teaspoon oil, add bread crumbs and garlic.
Cook for 5 minutes over medium heat or until browned.
Set aside.
In same skillet heat 2 tablespoons oil, pulp, onions, thyme and basil.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until eggplant is tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, bread crumbs, 1/2 cup almonds, ham, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place eggplant shells into large baking pan.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Top with Parmesan cheese and remaining almonds.
Sprinkle with paprika and remaining oil over cheese.
Add 1/2-inch boiling water to pan.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is browned.

title: candy bar salad
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add remainder of ingredients to liking.

title: liver in sauce(pork, beef or calves liver)
directions: Fry bacon and drain on paper towels.
Fry onion slices (rings) in bacon drippings.
Set aside.
Fry liver dipped in flour to coat.
Brown on each side.
Put in casserole dish; add onion and crumbled bacon on top.
Mix 1 can of tomato sauce with 1/2 can of water.
Add fennel seed and salt and pepper.
Pour over liver mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sauce is very good on mashed potatoes.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper and parsley.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots until done; drain.
Saute onion in butter.
In baking dish, layer carrots and cheese.
Pour onion and butter over top.
Crush Ritz crackers; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter, blend in flour and seasoning.
Add milk and cook until slightly thickened.
Add one cup of cheese and stir until cheese melts.
Cook macaroni, until tender and pour into a 2 inch deep casserole dish.
Pour sauce over macaroni in baking dish, top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: beef pot pie(from 1975 edition)
directions: To make dough squares:
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and butter.
Work together with fingertips.
Add combined milk with egg and knead into a firm mixture.
Cut in half and shape like pie crust.
Roll out on floured board thin, about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into large squares 1 1/2-inches.

title: turkey-in-the-straw soup
directions: Combine turkey and dressing, water, salt, pepper, parsley and thyme.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Add onion, celery and carrots.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Bring to a boil and add bouillon and noodles.
Simmer again until noodles are tender.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add apples and toss.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: wisconsin chili
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain.

In a large Dutch oven, put stewed tomatoes, tomato paste, beans, ground beef and macaroni. Add 1 to 2 cans of water to these ingredients to obtain your desired consistency. Add pepper and chili powder to your taste.
Simmer on low heat, stirring occasionally, for 2 hours.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk.
Add pineapple and other fruit.
Add juice of 2 lemons.
Mix well.
Pour in pie crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and bone chicken.
Blend 3 cups chicken broth with cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Bring to a boil.
Add egg noodles to remainder of chicken broth; cook until tender.
Drain noodles and pour into long pan.
Top with boned chicken.
Pour soup mixture over noodles and chicken.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top of soup.
Melt margarine and spoon over the cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: herb batter baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix egg and Ranch dressing.
Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Roll chicken in flour.
Dip into dressing mixture.
Roll chicken in cornflake crumbs.
Place on large foil-lined baking pan.
Bake until tender, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: potato bread
directions: *Use leftover mashed potatoes or frozen or instant made without the butter and salt.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Beat eggs and milk. Cream butter, sugar and spices. Add flour; mix well. Add soda to liquor and mix. Add fruit and nuts. Dough is easier to work with if refrigerated overnight.

title: clam chowder
directions: Chop clams.
Simmer with broth, butter and vegetables until vegetables are soft.
Remove from heat.
Let cool to room temperature.
Add seasoning.
Stir in can of evaporated milk and 1 gallon milk.
Heat over medium heat until hot.
Stir to prevent scorching.
Make paste of flour and milk.
Stir into hot milk to make soup as thick as desired.

title: beef potato casserole
directions: Pat beef in bottom of 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle soup mix over meat.
Pour soup over all.
Cover the top of the casserole with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spread cheese on top just before done.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add egg yolks.
Cream until light.
Add buttermilk and lemon extract.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted into pie.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Make a batter of eggs, milk, flour, baking powder and salt. Stir the oysters into the batter and drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat.
Cook until golden brown on each side.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In 2 qt. serving bowl (clear glass is nice) layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions. Spread salad dressing over onions, sealing to edge of bowl; cover. Chill several hours or overnight.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry cutter until shortening is the size of peas.
Add buttermilk, stirring until moistened.
Dough will resemble cottage cheese, but sticky.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.

title: garlic buttered green beans
directions: Cook green beans in water until tender.
Saute mushrooms in butter or oleo until tender.
Add onion and garlic powder.
Drain beans and add to mushrooms.
Toss.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: carrots supreme
directions: Boil carrots 15 to 30 minutes with 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Add onion; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to carrots. Serve cold.
May be kept in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: old english bread and butter pudding with whiskey sauce
directions: Grease baking dish with the butter. Cut the bread into quarters and soak in the milk for 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, combine the cream, eggs and sugar. Fold egg mixture and raisins into the bread/milk gently until combined.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until set.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix ingredients, except shrimp.
Stuff shrimp with mixed ingredients.
Bake at 395° for 25 minutes. Place under broiler for 1 minute; watch carefully.

title: stuffed manicotti shells
directions: Cook manicotti shells as directed on package; drain.
Mix onion, spinach, bouillon, garlic powder, thyme, cottage cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Fill manicotti shells with spinach mixture; arrange in a greased oblong pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Pour tomato sauce over manicotti; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Cover and cook in a 350° oven until hot and bubbly, about 25 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: orange chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in oil in skillet. In 9-inch square baking dish, pour contents of rice, margarine, water and orange juice. Place chicken on top. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and spoon marmalade over each chicken breast. Return to oven and bake an additional 10 minutes, uncovered. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: mrs. g. t. halls' chocolate icing
directions: Cook until 3 drops fall from spoon.
Stir until cool enough to spread on layers.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay out 3 large lengths of heavy-duty aluminum foil, each large enough to envelop one rack of ribs. Sprinkle the ribs with salt, pepper and m.s.g.
Enclose the ribs securely, sealing the foil so that the juice will not escape. Place the ribs in the oven and bake without opening the foil for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove the ribs from the oven, open the foil and let stand until ready to grill.
The juice in the foil may be added to the barbecue sauce or discarded.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Chop carrots, potatoes and onion; set aside.
Brown meat; drain.
Add chopped vegetables to meat; let steam 10 to 12 minutes.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, sauce and water.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve with hot corn bread.

title: enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas in hot grease to soften.
Put in 1 tablespoon of chili, sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Roll and place in baking dish.
Pour large can of enchilada sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
(I make my own sauce with onion, pepper and tomatoes.)
Cook, then pour over enchiladas.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals, then slice each oval lengthwise into matchsticks. Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of the vegetable oil.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and add water to cover.
Top with ice and let stand 1 1/2 hours. Drain and rinse vegetables.

title: vegetable antipasto
directions: In large skillet, combine all ingredients except olives. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Cool slightly.
Add olives. Transfer mixture to a bowl or storage container.
Cover.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: sweet-sour cole slaw
directions: Place shredded cabbage in covered dish in refrigerator for several hours.
Mix ingredients in order given 30 minutes before serving.
Chill and serve.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift into a mixing bowl first 4 dry ingredients.
In another bowl, mix eggs, milk and melted butter.
Pour the wet ingredients over the flour mixture.
Stir only enough to dampen the flour. Stir in the blueberries last.
Batter should not be smooth.
Spoon into buttered or paper lined muffin tins, having the tins about 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: appetizer onions
directions: You will need aluminum foil.

title: bonnie's orange sherbet
directions: Mix together; freeze in home freezer.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: texas beans
directions: Fry meat and onion.
Add catsup, mustard and brown sugar.
Add the beans and mix gently but well.
Bake in a pan at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil, eggs and sour cream.
Pour half the batter into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle over the batter in pan and add the rest of the batter; swirl together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vicki's scholarship cherry pie
directions: Combine sugar, 1/4 cup cherry juice and food coloring in heavy saucepan.
Cook to a rolling boil.
Add cherries and butter and cook 2 minutes.
Make smooth paste of cornstarch and 1/4 cup cherry juice.
Add to cherry mixture, stirring constantly and cook until thick.
Stir in lime juice and cinnamon.
Cool.

title: whole wheat teething biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients; knead until smooth.
Roll into sticks 1/4 x 5 inches.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm on oiled sheet, about 40 minutes.
Makes 60.

title: springtime salad
directions: In a saucepan, heat the pineapple and jello until jello is dissolved, but do not boil.
Let mixture cool, then mix in buttermilk and pecans. Fold in whipped topping and pour into a large bowl. Chill until firm.

title: country grits and sausage
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil; stir in grits.
Return to boil and reduce heat.
Cook 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine grits and cheese in a large mixing bowl; stir until cheese melts. Combine eggs, milk, thyme and garlic powder, mixing well.
Add a small amount of hot grits mixture to egg mixture, stirring well. Stir into remaining grits mixture.
Add crumbled sausage, stirring well.
Pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Garnish with tomato roses and parsley sprigs.
Yields 8 servings.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Pour over bread.
Cool and add the melted butter, sugar, eggs, salt, raisins and spice.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole that has been buttered.
Set the casserole in a pan of hot water 1 inch deep.
Bake at 350° until silver knife inserted in pudding comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Serve warm with lemon sauce if desired, or cream.

title: holiday ham
directions: Use a sharp knife to cut a crisscross pattern on the ham. Place cloves in the slits. Add the glaze. Bake another 30 minutes at 325°.

title: quick chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: summer italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, orange juice, Kool-aid, and sugar.
Add as much orange sherbet as you want to the mixture.
Put into a gallon jug and finish filling with water.
Keep in a cool place until time to serve.

title: sour cream coffee cake(yield: 12 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well, then add apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Place drained beets in a 1 1/2-quart jar.
Measure reserved liquid.
If necessary, add enough water to measure 1 cup.
In small saucepan, combine beet liquid, vinegar, sugar and salt; bring to boiling, stirring.
Pour over beets, then refrigerate, tightly covered, 24 hours.

title: hickory chip dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with potato chips, pretzels, crackers or carrots and celery.

title: mock lobster
directions: Season cod fillets with salt and pepper.
Lay on rack (a cake cooling rack works!) in a heavy, covered skillet.
Pour water into skillet to a level just below touching the cod.
Add 3 tablespoons vinegar and water; cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, until fish is cooked through.
Squeeze fresh lemon juice over (and if calories are no problem, melted butter).
Delicious!

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Roll in crushed nuts, and refrigerate.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix sugar, water and Kool-Aid and freeze.
Before time to serve, add pineapple juice and ginger ale.

title: green beans with tarragon dressing
directions: In a medium bowl, combine oil, vinegar, mustard, tarragon and garlic.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Add green beans. Toss to coat.

title: blake's cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll into snake.
Dip in melted butter. Roll around finger.
Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Put in oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: apple pudding
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Sift dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add to shortening mixture and stir well.
Add chopped apples.
Batter will be stiff.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown.

title: irish-italian spaghetti
directions: Cook onion in hot oil; add meat and seasonings and brown lightly.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add soups; cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cook spaghetti in salted, hot boiling water until tender.
Drain and rinse in hot water. Arrange spaghetti on hot plate; pour sauce over spaghetti.

title: hawaiian beef
directions: Drain pineapple chunks; reserve juice.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce and pepper; reserve.
Stir-fry beef with oil in a wok or skillet until brown.
Add green pepper and 2 tablespoons water to wok.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks, juice and tomatoes to the wok.
Add the reserved mixture.
Cook, stirring, until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and make into balls; chill.
Melt remaining ingredients in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Line bottom with graham crackers. Mix the vanilla instant pudding and milk until thick.
Add the Cool Whip.
Pour Cool Whip mixture over graham crackers.
Place another layer of graham crackers on top.
Ice with 1 can of chocolate frosting.
Chill.

title: custard pie perfect
directions: Combine eggs, salt and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cook for 30 minutes more.
You put this custard in an unbaked pie shell.
You sprinkle the cinnamon over the pie before cooking.

title: low-fat biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients to form dough.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Bake until golden brown, at 450° for approximately 10 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter together. Add rest of ingredients. Place in greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake the salmon, reserving liquid.
Chop onion and celery; saute in butter about 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and saute another 5 minutes.
Combine cooked vegetables with bread crumbs.
Add salmon, liquid, salt, pepper, parsley, lemon rind and lemon juice. Beat eggs lightly and add to salmon mixture with the milk.
Put salmon mixture in a large, greased loaf pan and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
6 to 8 servings.

title: tabbouleh(can be served as an appetizer or a side dish)
directions: Cover the bulgur with water and let it swell about 20 minutes. Drain well.
Arrange the lettuce leaves around the edge of 4 serving dishes.
Combine all the remaining ingredients with the bulgur and pile on the serving dishes.
Serve with warm pita bread, Souvlakia, Tzatziki, perhaps a tossed salad with oil and vinegar dressing and a light Italian ice for dessert.

title: cheesy vegetable sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart glass bowl.
Microwave at Medium-high for 2 minutes or until cheese melts, stirring at 1 minute intervals with a wire whisk.
Serve over cooked broccoli, cauliflower or even potatoes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add milk and blend.
Add eggs, blend. Add pumpkin and seasoning and mix well. Pour into crust.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.

title: lemon freeze pie
directions: Mix marshmallow cream with pie filling.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallow lemon mixture together.
Spread in pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 30 to 45 minutes before serving. Garnish with twisted, thin slices of lemon or lemon peel.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: small cream pie
directions: In a double boiler, combine sugar, salt and flour.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Add beer and stir to make a soft dough.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Set aside for 15 minutes to rise.
Bake in preheated oven at 375 degrees for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Wash and hull the strawberries.
Crush enough berries to make 1/2 cup.
Boil the crushed berries, sugar, water and cornstarch 2 minutes, stirring.
Add the butter.
Strain and cool.
Arrange the whole berries over the top of the cheesecake and pour the glaze over the berries.
Chill.

title: cinnamon delights
directions: Mix together first four ingredients until creamy. Trim edges off bread (square bread works best). Spread cream cheese mixture on bread slices. Roll up bread (jelly roll fashion). Brush with melted butter. Roll in sugar and cinnamon. Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 375°. This recipe is great to make and freeze the roll-up. Take out desired amount and place frozen on the cookie sheet in the oven. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chili rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Layer with green chilies and cheese. Place bay leaf on first layer.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening and then add eggs. Sift next 5 ingredients and add to the mixture. When well mixed, add the oatmeal and coconut (batter will be stiff). Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 13 minutes.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Mix all fruit with all flour.
Add the fruit and flour mixture to butter mixture.
Add eggs, then add spices.
Pour mixture into tube pans that have been greased and lined with brown paper.
Garnish cakes before cooking with pineapple (glazed) and cherries (glazed).
Cook about 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250°.
Put pan of water under the cakes in the oven for moisture.
Makes two cakes.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in syrup, flour and salt.
Bake 22 minutes at 350° on large cookie sheet or jelly roll pan, greased and floured.

title: oatmeal apple pudding
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish.
Mix together in baking dish the apples, sugar and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Pour over apples in greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: albino chili
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour and add sugar and shortening.
Mix well.
Soften yeast in warm water and add buttermilk.
Mix and knead well on floured surface.
Place in refrigerator in covered bowl.
Leave at least 2 hours.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well.
Chill for 1/2 hour in refrigerator.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Do not let them brown too much as they may dry out.
They can be made ahead and frozen.

title: banana-orange daiquiri
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a blender and process until smooth.
With the blender on, add the ice cubes 1 at a time and process until smooth.
The mixture will look like a thick slush. Garnish with orange slices, if desired.
Serve immediately.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together using electric mixer to be sure potatoes are mixed well.
Pour into a large baking dish.

title: easy saturday morning crumb cake
directions: Add the above to the sugar mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with the remaining crumbs and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: tandy cake
directions: Add melted butter to milk.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour into greased 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread peanut butter over warm cake.
Let cool. Spread melted chocolate over cold cake to cover.

title: happy hour biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together butter and sour cream.
Add flour and mix well.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls into greased mini-muffin pan.
Bake for 15 minutes. Remove biscuits from pan and let cool.
Slice biscuits in half.

title: jag
directions: Cook rice as directed and put paprika in water when cooking rice.
Slice linguica in circle halves.
Peel and chop onion. Cook linguica and onion together.
When done, add kidney beans and cook until beans are hot.
Add rice to mixture and serve warm.

title: breaded chicken
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs.
Add other ingredients and mix with fork; set aside.
Cut up chicken into pieces.
Skin chicken.
Dip chicken pieces into a dish of water, then into cracker crumb mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on doneness preferred.

title: tandy cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, flour, milk, oleo, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake this mixture on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While warm, spread top with peanut butter.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Melt chocolate bar and spread on top of peanut butter.
Cut in bars.

title: consomme rice
directions: Brown rice slightly in margarine; add consomme and onion soups.
Bake at 350° in covered casserole for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and peanut butter.
Stir in powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place on waxed paper.
Make a depression in center of each ball with back of spoon.
Fill each depression with 1/2 teaspoon melted chocolate.
Store, refrigerated.

title: banana bread
directions: Place butter, sugar and eggs in processor.
Blend until all ingredients are combined.
Add bananas and process again.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and add gradually. Blend until mixed well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggplant italiano
directions: Remove	skin
from
eggplant;	slice
1/8-inch
thick. Place slices on salted wet paper towel (top
and	bottom)
for 1/2 hour.
Rinse
slices
under cold water.
Dip
slices
in flour, then beaten
eggs
(which
contains garlic, salt, black pepper and parsley
flakes).
Dip in bread crumbs.
Brown both sides in oil; cool.
Layer casserole dish.
Put some spaghetti sauce on bottom of	dish.
Layer eggplant, cheese (Mozzarella and Cheddar), grated Romano
and sauce until used up.
Cover; bake at 350° for	45 minutes
to
1 hour.
Cool for 1/2 hour, slice and eat.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Cake should be put together in 3 steps.

title: mac's stew
directions: Stew hearts and gizzards until tender.
Add potatoes, carrots, onion, celery, salt, black pepper and garlic salt and boil until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add Crisco, salt and milk.
Stir until mixed well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Beat until right consistency to spread.
Will cover 3 layer cake.

title: cheese-stuffed chicken in phyllo(makes 8 servings)
directions: Place each chicken breast half between two sheets of heavy plastic wrap.
Pound with the flat side of a meat mallet until 1/8-inch thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: ice cream squares
directions: Mix
graham
cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: layered taco bake
directions: Add taco seasoning to beef as if you were making tacos; set aside.
Crush chips in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Then sprinkle meat mixture; then sour cream; then Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until cheese melts.
Sprinkle with lettuce, tomato, etc.
Just like a taco!

title: spread for ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on buns.
Put ham and Swiss cheese on.
Wrap in foil.
Warm 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Freezes well.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix together chopped nuts, 1/2 c. sugar and cinnamon to make topping.
Separately, combine remaining ingredients to form a batter.
Spread half of the batter in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle half of the topping.
Then repeat with remaining batter and topping.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Mix ingredients together and knead.
Roll into ball and press into miniature cupcake tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in quart jar.
Keep in icebox. This will keep several weeks.

title: oriental salad
directions: Melt butter in skillet and brown the noodles and almonds.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender; peel and slice thinly into bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp; cook onion in bacon drippings until yellow.
Remove from pan and reserve.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of fat from frypan.
Mix in flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in water and vinegar; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over the potatoes, along with the bacon and onion; stir to mix.
Can be kept warm in oven until ready to serve.

title: yummy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Begin by melting caramels and 1/3 cup of
Pet
milk.
Mix
melted margarine, 1/3 cup Pet milk and cake mix.
Pour
of
cake mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for
minutes.
Remove
and sprinkle chocolate morsels, then pour
melted
caramels
and pecans.
Top with rest of cake mixture, bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; stir in butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Spread out like a crust in a 10-inch pie plate.
Make filling.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Separate egg whites and whip egg whites until fluffed (partial).
Mix thoroughly all ingredients in large bowl with exception of milk.
Pour ingredients into ice cream maker and pour milk to fill line.
Ice down; mix until frozen.
Be sure to use plenty of salt to the ice to lower temperature of ice.

title: buttermilk salad dressing
directions: Pour all ingredients in small jar with tight fitting lid. Shake until well blended.
Refrigerate.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Overnight makes it better.
Shape into patties.
Fry brown on both sides.

title: christmas date roll
directions: Cook milk and sugar
to
a
soft ball stage.
Add dates and stir until well
mixed
and
then
cook
to
the hard ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add nuts and vanilla and cool until it can be kneaded.
Shape
in
long roll in cloth wrung out of cold water. Roll in sugar, then wrap in wax paper.
The candy will keep indefinitely and is moist and delicious.

title: green pepper jelly
directions: Seed and chop peppers.
Put 1/2 of the peppers and 1/2 the vinegar into a blender and puree.
Repeat with remaining 1/2.
Put puree into a large pan with cayenne, sugar and salt.
Stir constantly as you bring it to a full boil.
Add pectin and boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat and add green coloring to achieve suitable color.
Pour into sterile jars and seal with paraffin. Makes 2 pints.

title: apricot-pineapple jam
directions: In large saucepan mix all ingredients except sugar.
Let stand 1 hour.
Then cook slowly until apricots are tender.
Add sugar and cook slowly, stirring frequently until thick and clear (220°) on candy jelly thermometer.
Pour at once into hot sterilized glasses and seal with paraffin.
Cover with lids.
Makes about 6 (6-ounce) glasses.
Just the right jam for every sweet tooth.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour over cut up apples.
Add a little water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until apples are done.

title: green bean cake
directions: Drain green beans, dissolve sugar into water.
Put beans in, let bake for 1 hour.
Slice beans into small pieces and lay in bottom of pan.
Bake cake according to package directions.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients thoroughly by hand, then add Rice Krispies.
Put rounded teaspoonful on cookie sheet and flatten with fork.

title: chocolate chip
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl and beat on medium speed until creamy.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda into creamed mixture until blended well.
Drop rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: kitty's mock cheese souffle
directions: Butter bread pieces and cut in quarters.
In a buttered casserole, place a layer of bread, then a layer of cheese to make 4 layers.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 hours, a must.
Bake in pan of water at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: joyce's punch ring
directions: Heat water and sugar together until syrupy. Add juices. Freeze

title: raw apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs.
Add oil and Sugar Twin to eggs.
Mix in apples.
Sift flour with baking soda and baking powder.
Add to mixture with fork.
Add raisins, nuts and vanilla. Bake for 35 minutes in 8-inch square pan coated with Pam.
Can be served warm with whipped cream or frosted with powdered sugar. Keep refrigerated.

title: pecan squares
directions: Cream together 1 cup brown sugar and butter.
Add egg. Gradually add flour.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Brush on 1 egg. Sprinkle on 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Sprinkle on pecans.
Sprinkle on 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes (allow them to cool before cutting).
Makes approximately 24 cookies.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Dice and saute sausage, potato and onion in large skillet. Brown and add tomato pieces.
Crack eggs and stir until well blended as if you're scrambling the eggs in large bowl.
Add milk; stir.
When sausage mixture is browned, add egg mixture and scramble.
When the eggs are cooked, put them into the burrito shells (about 3/4 cup into each) and wrap shells around egg mixture.
Put two stuffed burritos in foil and bake for 15 minutes.

title: pesto
directions: Pick off washed basil leaves from stem.
Blend in food processor leaves, tomatoes and garlic.
Add oil until very moist but not runny.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add pesto to mayonnaise for a great taste or serve with pasta.

title: quick chicken chili
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes.
Saute in vegetable oil until brown.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream, shredded cheese or sliced green onions, if desired.

title: barbecue moose ribs
directions: Boil moose ribs for 45 minutes and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread over ribs in baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes or until tender, maybe up to an hour, at 350°.

title: hungarian gulyas
directions: Brown onion in a large frying pan in Crisco. Add paprika, green pepper and carrot.
Add meat to pan and let it simmer until tender, covered.
Stir it with a wooden spoon.
You may add a potato (quartered) with some water to pan or boil shell pasta and add to pan.
Season with salt, pepper and caraway seed.

title: graham cracker cookie
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and evaporated milk 3 minutes after mixture comes to a full boil.
Add marshmallows.
When melted, add graham crackers or vanilla wafers, pecans and coconut.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool and serve.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish and preheat oven to 350°. Steam broccoli 3 minutes, cool and press dry.
Beat together the eggs and milk until frothy.
Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt, then stir into the egg mixture and mix well.
Fold the broccoli, cheese and onion into the mixture.
Spoon the mixture into the dish and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting into bite-size pieces.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine chicken, celery, almonds, salt, onions, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Place in lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese and chips.
Bake in preheated 425° oven 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with snack crackers or fancy bread.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix well with electric mixer.
Finish filling freezer with homogenized milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: rose petal beads
directions: Gather fresh rose petals and grind them in a meat grinder or a modern food processor.
Place the pulp and juice into an old iron skillet or pot.
It must be iron, not a modern coated pan.
The iron causes the petals to turn black.
Let the pulp stand in the skillet for a day, but stir it occasionally.
It should be dry in about a day.
Grind it again, dry it, grind again for 9 days.

title: cajun rice
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Add broth, pepper, chili powder, thyme, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes. Fluff.

title: ham and cheese cake
directions: Spray 9-inch spring-form pan with Pam and add bread crumbs to bottom of pan and pat in place.

title: spinach balls or patties
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well.
Mix spinach and remaining ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls or patties.
Place on Pam sprayed cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
If making patties, turn over after 10 minutes.
Makes 36 (1-inch) balls or about 12 to 14 patties. Contains 41 calories per ball.

title: crock-pot cheese potatoes
directions: Cook about 10 potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash potatoes.
Cook milk, cheese, butter and salt until smooth and stir into mashed potatoes.
Fold in eggs.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until brown.

title: caramel marshmallow pops on a stick
directions: Place caramels, butter and sweet milk in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until candy and butter melt and mixture is smooth.
Pour cereal in a 9 x 13-inch pan and set aside.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nuts. Set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add zucchini and pineapple. Add dry ingredients.
Stir only until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool about 10 minutes before removing to wire rack.

title: charlie's italian-style salmon steaks
directions: Preheat broiler or heat coals in an outdoor grill.
Place salmon steaks in single layer in a shallow baking dish.
Combine Italian dressing, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pour over salmon. Let salmon sit for 30 minutes, turning once. Drain salmon. Reserve marinade for basting.
Place the salmon on a well-greased grill rack or broiler pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook about 4-inches from coals or broiler heat source for 8 minutes.
Baste with marinade.
Sprinkle with more paprika.
Turn salmon over and cook for 7 to 10 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: pineapple cherry crumbcake
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan as listed.
Pour melted margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: cut-it-out cookies
directions: In a bowl beat butter on medium speed until softened.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well. Gradually add flour and mix well.
Divide mix into 4 parts and chill in plastic wrap.
Roll on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with
circular cookie cutter; bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: chezze grits
directions: Put in microwave for 1 minute.
Take out and stir good.
Then you have cheese grits.

title: city chicken legs
directions: You will need 12 wooden sticks.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add taco seasoning and let cool. Combine all other ingredients *.
Add cooled hamburger.
Add as much salad dressing as desired (mayonnaise/Thousand Island dressing).

title: old-fashioned sugar cream pie
directions: Heat milk to warm with butter until butter melts.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together with fingers until well-blended.
Pour into milk mixture, stirring constantly until it thickens.
It will bubble like grits.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Mix well and pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nutmeg on top.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet-sour greens
directions: Discard stems of greens and any damaged portions.
Thoroughly wash greens in cool water to remove dirt and sand particles.
Cut or tear leaves into small pieces.
In covered saucepan, cook greens in large amount of boiling salted water till tender, about 60 to 75 minutes.
Drain well and rinse.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon and set aside.
Blend flour into drippings.
Add hot water; cook and stir till thickened and bubbly.
Stir in sugar, cider vinegar, salt and pepper.
Stir in drained, cooked greens; heat thoroughly.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice.
Mix eggs, vanilla, milk, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour over rice.
Mix and bake in a casserole dish at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Thaw chicken breasts.
Put in pan and cover with water.
Add onion, parsley, salt and pepper; bring to boil.
Turn down and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Remove meat and cool.
Remove meat from bone.
Save broth for sauce.

title: quiche
directions: Make recipe for 2 pie crusts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer ham, then onion, then Swiss cheese over pie crust.
Mix eggs, cream and spices.
Pour over layered pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: mexican pralines
directions: Cook sugars and water together	to
240° or to the soft ball stage.
Just before
removing
from
fire,	add
nuts and vanilla. Beat until sort of
creamy.
Pour in large rounds on wax paper.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix everything together for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a Bundt pan.

title: mama's "fertilizer" sweet pickles
directions: Cook together vinegar, green food coloring, sugar and salt. Put in a bag the whole cloves, mixed spices and celery seed. Bring to a full boil and pour over cucumbers and let stand overnight.
Heat and let cook 35 minutes.
Then fill and seal jars.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
These can be made ahead and reheated at serving time either in the oven or the microwave.

title: sweet fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits. Mix the first four ingredients with the sour cream. It should be mixed a few hours before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and drain.
Add remaining ingredients; reserve 1/2 of bread crumbs for the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add pecans and flour.
Press into bottom of 33-23-5 cm dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; cool.

title: cabbage & bean soup
directions: In dutch oven brown beef.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruits and juices together; add pudding mix in and stir until
dissolved in juices well. Chill 1 hour.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, margarine, syrup, salt and vanilla. Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in baking soda. Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Bake in a 250° oven for
1 hour.
Stir several times while baking.
Pour out on waxed paper to cool.

title: jello cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar with mixer, beating until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased round 8 or 9-inch layer pans. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a tightly covered jar.
Shake well until dressing is thoroughly mixed.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Shake well before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: quiche muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fill large, greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
This recipe makes about 10 of the large muffins or 15 cupcake size.
On the large size muffins, cooking time was about 25 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Crush wafers and sprinkle in pan.
Add in layers the coconut, chips and pecans. Add milk. Do not stir.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned fudge pie
directions: Mix together with a spoon, not a mixer.
Bake pie shell a few minutes before pouring batter into shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: In top
of double boiler, melt chocolate chips over hot water. Remove
from
heat,
but
leave
over
hot water.
Add sweetened condensed milk, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Turn into a wax paper lined 8-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into small squares.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: "fancy fudge ribbon cake"
directions: Cream 2 tablespoons butter with cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 egg, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Set aside.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in pretty glass bowl; use whatever amount of each that it takes to fill bowl almost to the top.
Of course you can use your own choice of vegetables and in the order you prefer to put them in (this is just my preference).
Then cover the top with a thick coat of mayonnaise.
To me, the homemade mayo is what makes this salad special.
Sprinkle grated cheese generously over mayonnaise, then bacon on top of cheese.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Simmer onion in oil and water until transparent.
Add potatoes and carrots; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chopped tomatoes (save juice) and cumin.
Cover; simmer for about 1 hour, checking to see if stew needs more liquid.
If so, add the juice from can of tomatoes.
