If more liquid is still needed, you can add up to 3/4 cup of tomato juice.
Add green beans; cook for 15 minutes more.
Check seasoning.
Add 1/4 teaspoon or more of pepper and more cumin, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: bonanza beans
directions: Cover beans with water.
Soak overnight.
Next morning add all other ingredients to the beans.
Cook until beans are done but not too soft.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place into glass cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: beefy mexicali rice
directions: In large skillet or electric frying pan, bring water to a boil.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese, breaking up the meat into small pieces.
Reduce heat; cover dish and simmer, stirring occasionally, cook 12 minutes or until rice is tender and most liquid is absorbed.
Top with cheese; cover and let stand 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: spicy franks
directions: Place wieners in slow cooker.
In separate bowl, combine chili sauce, barbecue sauce and cranberry sauce.
Pour over wieners.
Cover.
Cook on low 3 to 4 hours or high 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Yield: 4 to 6 full-sized servings, or 32 appetizer-sized servings.

title: crispy sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls (about 75).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen before or after baking.

title: favorite chocolate sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add water and milk; bring to boiling point.
Continue to boil for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; beat with spoon for about 2 minutes.
Good over hot fudge cake or ice cream. Serve cold or hot.

title: melody's chocolate pie
directions: Put all ingredients into saucepan except vanilla.
Cook on top
of
stove
over
medium
heat.
Stir until thick; add vanilla and
thicken
some more.
Pour into baked pie shells. Chill or let cool before cutting.

title: seven layer dip
directions: In a 12-inch round deep dish (sides 1-inch), layer the ingredients.
Spread bean dip; spread guacamole on top.
Mix taco seasoning with sour cream and spread on guacamole.
Spread onion on next.
Spread chopped tomatoes next.
Then spread grated cheese and sliced olives.
Serve with large bag of plain tostada chips.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand in a large mixing bowl.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool for 15 minutes.
Turn onto plate.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: vegetable tortilla rounds(appetizer)
directions: Mix cream cheese, dressing mix and a bit of milk to get creamy but firm texture.
Add onions.
Spread on tortillas.
Add finely chopped vegetables.
Roll up and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Must be firm before slicing and serving.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of pretty ovenproof dish.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Next layer chopped peppers over chili. Cover with grated cheese.
Heat in oven or microwave until cheese melts, no longer.
Serve hot with chips.

title: chocolate icebox cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients, except sugar.
Cream butter and sugar and add syrup.
Beat in all ingredients (dry).
When thoroughly mixed, add nuts and work with hands until stiff dough is formed.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one. Mix soda and bananas. Add flour to butter mixture alternating with bananas, then add vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased/floured 4-1/2 x 8-1/2 inch loaf pan or 3 smaller ones. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: alabama chocolate-praline jumbo christmas mud squares
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, stirring well.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: peanut butter finger bars and frosting
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine all bar and frosting ingredients except chocolate chips at low speed until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Press into bottom of prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle immediately with chocolate chips.
Let stand 5 minutes; spread evenly.
In small bowl, combine all glaze ingredients.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften 2 cheeses and mix well with other ingredients.
Use hands to form into ball-shape.
Roll in parsley.
Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar until smooth; add the egg yolks and blend well.
Mix the buttermilk and baking soda and add to the mixture.
Blend in the flour and vanilla.
Melt the chocolate in the hot water and add.
Mix well.
Beat the egg whites until stand in peaks; fold into the cake batter.
Pour batter into 4 layer cake pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Check to see when done. Remove from oven and cool on racks.
Frost with the following.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Combine broth, chicken, celery, carrots, onion, parsley, pepper, thyme and bay leaf in a large saucepan or Dutch oven. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, stirring once or twice. Reduce heat to low; simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink in center.
Remove bay leaf; discard.
Stir in rice and lime juice.
Garnish, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, egg and peanut butter together until well mixed.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Mix into cheese and mayonnaise.
Cook in glass casserole or pie plate at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.
(Triscuits are best!)

title: blue cheese whip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat together Blue cheese and 1/4 cup sour cream. Fold in remaining sour cream.
Cover and chill.
Serve as a spread for crackers, as a "dunk" for breadsticks and celery or as a filling for celery stalks.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Place sugar, chocolate, light corn syrup, butter and salt in a saucepan and heat slowly, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Cover until boiling point is reached.
Cook without stirring until temperature is 240°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Beat until creamy, adding milk until mixture loses its shine.
Pour into a greased square pan.
Cut into squares.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, butter and brown sugar and blend with mixer until particles are fine.
Stir in walnuts.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture for topping.
Press remainder of mixture into ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over crust.
Sprinkle with the reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and sour cream
directions: Cook chicken in crock-pot until tender. Remove from bone. Cut into chunks. Mix chicken soup with half can of chicken broth. Pour half of mixture in bottom of casserole dish. Layer chicken on top of mixture.
Pour in rest of mixture. Spread container of sour cream on top. Prepare stuffing by directions. Spread over sour cream.
Put pats of butter on top. Bake in preheated oven at 350° until browned and sour cream bubbles.

title: shrimp and rice salad with curry
directions: Combine first five ingredients and mix well. In a separate bowl, combine the remaining ingredients. Mix well. If needed, thin with the pineapple juice. Fold into the rice and shrimp mixture. Refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: french buttercream cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine ingredients.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Shape
into 3/4-inch balls.
Place, 2 inches apart, on cookie sheet; flatten with fork.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes.
Don't let get brown.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread evenly the Cool Whip over top of mixture.
Keep cool in refrigerator until served.

title: christmas cake and icing
directions: Mix as directed on cake mix box, but add the coconut to the mixture.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans.
When done, cool on cake rack.
When completely cooled, cut the cakes so you will have 4 layers instead of 2 layers.
Put icing on top of each layer but not on sides.
Sprinkle the top with more coconut.

title: pumpkin dessert ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 2 quart ring mold.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening, water, nuts, raisins, and pumpkin.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with mixer or give 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Scrape bowl constantly.
Add egg.
Beat 2 more minutes, scraping bowl constantly.
Pour into prepared mold.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with fluffy hard sauce, lemon sauce, or whipped cream.
Yield:
8 portions.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Mix in eggs and beat well. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan greased and floured.
Do not preheat oven.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet with a little cooking oil on both sides.
Place in baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup, water and seasonings together, pour over chops.
Slice onion and arrange on top of chops.
Bake in 350° oven until chops are tender.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix sugars, oil and eggs together.
Add zucchini, then mix flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to the first mixture.
Pour into cake pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Enjoy!

title: hot dog stew
directions: Saute chopped onion and add tomato sauce and water to desired thickness.
Add hot dogs and diced potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until potatoes are cooked.

title: nuts 'n bolts
directions: Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: quick cherry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pie filling.
Pour into mold, if desired, and chill.
Whipped topping is good on the top.
Serves about 6.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in large saucepan.
Remove bacon; pour off all but 3 tablespoons drippings.
Add onion, separated into rings; cook until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling; simmer a minute or two.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: "jordan marsh" blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add alternately with dry ingredients and milk.
Add blueberries. Butter muffin tins.
Pile batter high in tins.
Sprinkle sugar over tops.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: blackberry wine cooler
directions: In a glass with ice, pour jigger of wine and ginger ale; mix well.
Enjoy.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl; mix well.
Pour over any beef (especially good for London broil or flank steak) in a glass baking dish or self-closing plastic bag.
Let marinate in refrigerator up to three days.
Grill or broil, as desired, discarding marinade.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: In soup pot, brown bacon.
Remove bacon and most fat.
Add onion; saute until tender.
Add crumbled bacon and all other ingredients except clams.
Simmer, covered, 30 to 40 minutes.
Add clams and heat through.
Do not overcook clams; they will get tough.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla and stir by hand. Add blueberries and mix gently.
Grease muffin tins. Fill to top of cups and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pan.
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat with salt in skillet.
Drain and set aside.
Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onions and pepper.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown on top.

title: poor man's seafood primavera
directions: In 12-inch skillet or small stewing pot, over medium heat, heat milk, bouillon and vegetables to boiling, stirring frequently.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Shake in bag with cinnamon and sugar.
Do a few at a time and make sure they are well covered (you may need to use more sugar and cinnamon).
Empty the remaining sugar and cinnamon into bottom of greased Bundt pan. Place half of biscuits in pan.
Melt 3/4 cup butter and pour over biscuits.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Repeat layer of biscuits.

title: real homemade biscuits
directions: In large bowl, mix together, leaving flour around edge of bowl.
Pat well into ball.
Spread on sheet paper, patting out. Cut into 1 dozen or more biscuits.
Grease pan, oiling top and bottom of biscuit.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: challah bread(easter bread)
directions: Mix 1 1/4 cups flour, the yeast, sugar and salt.
Heat water and 1 tablespoon oil until very warm.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat 1 minute.
Beat in egg until smooth.
Stir in flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours until doubled.
Grease cookie sheet.
Punch down dough and divide into 3 parts.
Roll into a 14-inch long rope.
Place on cookie sheet and braid loosely.
Do not stretch.
Form a wreath and secure ends.
Brush with oil.
Cover and let double about 40 to 50 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Mix egg yolk and 2 tablespoons water.
Brush over braid.
Sprinkle with poppy seeds.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Brown lightly.
Remove from sheet to cool on rack. Place colored easter eggs in center for festive gift or centerpiece.

title: oatmeal chewies(cookies)
directions: The night before: Mix together oats, sugar and oil.
The next morning: Mix remaining ingredients; mix into first mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture along with bananas, blending well.
Stir in nuts. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan that is greased well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar and remaining ingredients in order given. Bake in a preheated very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes. Reduce heat quickly (leave door slightly ajar about 3 minutes to slow oven to 325°) and continue baking for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center of filling. Serve warm or cold.

title: poor man's steak and gravy
directions: Mix ground beef, cracker crumbs, salt, pepper, milk and onion. Form in loaf pan and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and fry until brown
on both sides.
Remove from pan.
Put slices in a 9	x 13-inch
pan
and
pour 2 cans of mushroom soup and water.	Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: grape-nut bread(2 loaves)
directions: Mix the Grape-Nuts and buttermilk together; let stand 1 hour. After Grape-Nuts and buttermilk have set for 1 hour, add to remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan; batter will be thick.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours in a 325° oven.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar, soda and buttermilk in medium size saucepan. Place over moderate heat (250°).
Cook, stirring occasionally, until a small amount of the syrup forms soft ball when dropped into ice water or candy thermometer registers 236°.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts; beat with wooden spoon until slightly thickened.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until set.
Makes about 16 pieces.

title: country cooked green beans
directions: In a heavy pot, pour 2 quarts of water, meat, sugar and salt. Let boil while preparing beans.
Wash beans well.
Add to boiling mixture.
After cooking about 1 hour, add onion.
Let cook until liquid is low.

title: fresh salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use chips or pour over burritos.

title: campsite kielbasa
directions: Slice sausage in half lengthwise, then slice sausage 3/4-inch thick in half moon shapes.
Slice onion and peppers into strips. Slice the potatoes.
Drain liquid from water chestnuts.
Place all ingredients in a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.
When camping, vegetables can be prepared before you leave and stored in Ziploc bags.
The sausage should be left in its original wrapping and prepared that night before cooking.

title: fruit slush
directions: Thaw frozen ingredients.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Mix well.
Freeze until firm.
Thaw for 30 minutes.
Stir until slushy.
Spoon into glasses.

title: mammy's white cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Pour in milk and vanilla.
Add flour and other dry ingredients, beating after each addition.
Beat an additional two minutes.
Pour into tube pan which has been greased and coated with sugar.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
This is delicious; does not need frosting.

title: easy bisquick lasagne squares
directions: Grease a square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix cooked ground beef with herbs, tomato paste and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese in a separate bowl.
Set aside.
In the baking dish, place a layer of cottage cheese, then layer of Parmesan cheese, then beef mixture, evenly.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper with a wire whisk until smooth, approximately 1 minute.
Pour over top of meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for approximately 35 minutes. Sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Melt butter, add cocoa and water.
Stir constantly until thickened.	Do Not Boil.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and gradually add confectioners sugar, beating with whisk until smooth.

title: heavenly biscuits
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water, then stir to dissolve.
Set aside.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add shortening and blend, using a pastry blender or a food processor until mixture resembles crumbs.
Add buttermilk to yeast mixture and stir well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Boil the 2 cups water, cloves, allspice and stick cinnamon in a small pan for 5 minutes.
Drain and add to the lemon and orange juice and the sugar.
Fill the pan with water.
Bring to boil and add 3 tea bags.
Boil 5 minutes.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch pan, mixing well. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Combine milk, butter and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Pour over warm cake.
Cool for several hours before cutting.

title: summer cake
directions: Punch holes in top of cake with fingers.
Pour crushed pineapple over cake, juice and all.
Mix vanilla pudding and let set in fridge.
Add coconut to pudding; spread mixture over cake.
Top with layer of Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecan halves.

title: corn souffle
directions: Make a white sauce of the butter, flour and milk.
Add the beaten eggs, salt, 1/4 cup grated cheese and corn.
Put into greased casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Top with 1/4 cup additional cheese the last 10 minutes.

title: cheese salad
directions: Whip the pimento cheese and add the Cool Whip, pineapple and miniature marshmallows.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt, oleo and vanilla and mix well. Add vinegar and mix well.
Mix in eggs and pecans; stir well. Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: "can't stop with one" pickles
directions: Drain
liquid
from
pickles
and slice crosswise.
Add sugar, vinegar,
onion
and cinnamon, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Refrigerate
for 24 hours, stirring several times. Pickles will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat (drain extra grease); add soups and milk.
Stir. Line bottom of casserole dish with chips.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over chips.
Layer more chips, then the rest of the mixture.
Pour enchilada sauce over all and put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: corn and salmon loaf
directions: Open can of salmon.
Get all the skin and bones out, then mix salmon and corn together.
Get your bread and break into tiny pieces; put half of it in salmon and corn mix and put other half on top of corn and salmon loaf.
Mix all the other ingredients. Bake on 300° for 1/2 hour to 1 hour until it plum back in center.

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage roll
directions: Season ground beef with salt, pepper and beaten egg.
Mix in uncooked rice.
Brown butter; add onion, celery and parsley.
Add sugar, lemon and tomato soup.
You can use tomato juice.
Dip cabbage head in boiling water to loosen leaves.
Put one spoonful of meat mixture on leaf.
Roll lightly.
Cover with sauce.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make vanilla pudding.
Cut up the bananas.
Add the bananas to the mixture.
Add the vanilla wafers.
Add the Cool Whip; let set.

title: chocolate mint pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch in a medium-size saucepan. Add milk, mixing until smooth.
Cook until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add small amount of cornstarch mixture to egg yolk mixture; mix well.
Add this mixture back to cornstarch mixture.
Cook until mixture boils. Add mint.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or until set.

title: pass the mustard salad dressing
directions: In a blender, mix vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper, garlic powder, honey and sugar until thoroughly combined.
With the motor running, VERY SLOWLY drizzle in oil until fully incorporated. Store in refrigerator.
Makes 2 - 1/2 cups.
Great on a spinach salad.

title: gary's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Put hamburger and everything else in big
pot.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low.
Great for cold, winter days.
Any left over can be frozen.
Guaranteed to warm you up!

title: corn salad
directions: Combine corn, tomato, cucumber, celery, peppers and onions. Stir in salad dressing.
Mix well.	Chill for several hours and serve.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat eggs.
Add corn and muffin mix.
Blend and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine tomatoes, cucumber, onion, chilies and coriander. Stir together lemon juice and salt.
Add to vegetables and mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: cheese-onion-bacon bread
directions: In large bowl dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add warm milk, sugar, salt and margarine.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add 1 cup more flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in cheese, bacon and onion.
Add remaining 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour slowly.
Make a soft dough.
Place on floured board.
Cover and let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Knead 10 minutes until smooth and blistered.
Place in warm place to rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again. Divide into 2 loaves and place in greased bread pans.
Cover and let rise again.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes until done. Remove from pan immediately.
Brush top with butter.
Cool on racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add the remaining ingredients and beat well.
Bake in 12 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and leave in pan as this cake is very moist and can not be taken out.

title: easy italian dip
directions: Mix the ingredients and serve with apples, assorted vegetables, crackers and chips.

title: quick dumplings
directions: Bring broth to a boil.	Mix about 1/2 or 1 cup broth in with flour.
Add Crisco into flour mixture.
Stir mixture into a soft ball
and
put on wax paper to roll out.
Roll out and make it stiff.
Cut strips and squares of dough and drop into boiling broth.
Add
the chicken and margarine.
Let low boil until liquid has a soupy texture to it.

title: smooth pralines
directions: Combine sugars, corn syrup, water and vinegar in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add butter, butterscotch chips, vanilla and pecans.
Stir until butterscotch chips are melted. Drop from tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Makes about 18 to 20.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream margarine and shortening together.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well after each addition.
Sift flour and salt.
Add lemon to milk.
Add 1/2 of flour and 1/2 of milk to egg mixture; mix.
Add remaining flour and milk; beat for about 15 minutes.
Pour into tube pan; bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool for 10 minutes; turn out on cake plate.

title: pollack hungarian goulash
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add your chopped onions.
Mix to this mixture cream-style corn and red beans.
Pour this mixture over a package of wide noodles that you've already cooked.
Serves 8.

title: banana bread(this recipe would delight any monkey's heart.)
directions: Mix the eggs in a large bowl, then add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Place in a greased loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: mexican relish
directions: Grind together and mix with salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Put in a bag and drain overnight.
In a.m. mix sugar, mustard seed and vinegar to drained pepper mixture.
Boil 10 minutes and can in hot jars.

title: warm salad of grilled shrimp, scallops and endive
directions: Mix together 2 tablespoons of the olive oil, juice of 1 lemon, 2 cloves garlic, fennel seed and salt and pepper.
Place shrimp and scallops in bowl; pour oil and lemon mixture over them and toss.
Cover and refrigerate for an hour.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray 10 x 15-inch pan with nonstick spray. Melt margarine and mix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Dip chicken breasts in margarine.
Coat with breadcrumb mixture.
Place in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: double corn cakes
directions: Stir together pancake mix and corn meal.
Combine corn, milk, eggs and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Drop batter from 1/4 cup onto hot, lightly greased griddle or skillet.
Turn once.
Makes about 16 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: french silk frosting
directions: Beat powdered sugar, margarine, chocolate and vanilla in small mixer bowl on low speed.
Add milk gradually. Beat until smooth and fluffy.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl, except bread, and mix well. Slice the loaf of bread into 1-inch slices.
Spread garlic cheese mixture on each slice of bread.
Bake on baking sheet 12 to 15 minutes in a preheated oven at 350°.

title: mother's chili
directions: In a 5-quart saucepan, combine dry red beans with water. Allow to stand overnight.
When ready to cook, pour off only that amount of water necessary to have beans covered.
Cover and cook 1 1/2 hours, adding more water as needed.
To beans add tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, bay leaf, catsup, chili powder, lemon juice, vinegar, salt, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, garlic powder and cooked ground beef.
Cover and simmer about 3 hours.
Add chopped celery, onion and bell pepper and continue to simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Serve piping hot.

title: carrot brownies
directions: Melt butter; stir in well the brown sugar.
Beat in eggs. Beat in flour.
Add baking powder, salt and grated carrots.
Pour into two 8-inch greased pans.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Combine sugar and butter in bowl; add hot milk.
Cool; add yeast.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Add flour and salt.
Dough will be soft.
Knead very little.
Let dough rise in bowl.
Press out to 1 inch thick; cut with large cutter.
Dip in melted butter; fold in half.
Place on 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: refrigerator white rolls
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine the milk, shortening, sugar, and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup of flour; beat well.
Beat in yeast mixture and egg.
Add remaining flour; mix well.
Place in greased bowl; grease surface.
Cover; store in refrigerator at least 2 hours or until needed.
About 1 1/2 to 2 hours before serving time, shape dough on well-floured surface. Let rise in warm place until double (about 1 1/4 hours).
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 16 medium rolls.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell. Cook at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: skillet potatoes, onions and beans
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well; do not peel. Cut into thin slices.

Heat shortening in a large skillet. Add potatoes and onions slowly, turning carefully as vegetables brown lightly. When cooked, add beans and water. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring to prevent sticking.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed. Cool and split into 4 layers. Drain strawberries. Mix sour cream, Cool Whip, sugar and strawberries. Spread in between layers and over cake.

title: chop suey
directions: Pour boiling water over bouillon cubes and soy sauce.
Stir until smooth; set aside.
Saute pork in Crisco until brown.
Add flour; stir and blend.
Add other ingredients.
Cook, covered, slowly.
Stir often.
Cook 30 minutes.
Good over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: filled coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Stir in baking powder, salt, milk and flour.
Put half the batter in prepared pan.
In a small bowl, mix 1 cup brown sugar, 4 teaspoons cinnamon, nuts and 1/4 cup butter.
Spread this mixture over batter in pan.
Pour remaining batter over filling.
In a small bowl, mix topping ingredients and spread topping evenly over top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: fruit-nut bread
directions: Follow directions on nutbread mix (less water).
Mix all together. Put in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Check at 35 minutes with tester in center.
May need few more minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skin.
Cool, peel and shred.
Add grated cheese and mix together.
Combine butter, soup, salt and green onion in a saucepan and heat through.
Add sour cream to soup mixture and stir.
Pour over potatoes and cheese and mix thoroughly.
Bake, uncovered, in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together in large bowl eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin; set aside.
Mix together in another bowl remaining ingredients.
Mix contents of both bowls together.
Pour in ungreased 10 x 15 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Pumpkin Bar Frosting.

title: "slim" sour cream
directions: Put cottage cheese in blender.
Add buttermilk and salt. Blend on low speed about 1 minute.
Can be used on baked potatoes or in dips.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper, water chestnuts, mushrooms and half can of French fried onions.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cheez Whiz or grated Cheddar cheese and remaining French fried onions.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, coconut and pecans.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
As soon as cake is out of oven, spread one 7 ounce jar of marshmallow cream over cake.
Let cool.
Frost.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted ingredients and beat well.
Form into small loaf 1 1/2-inch in diameter.
Chill.
Slice and arrange half slices on greased cookie sheet.
Place 1 teaspoon date filling and top with another slice. Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits, mandarin oranges and cherries.
Pour canned peach pie filling in a large bowl and add all other ingredients.
Mix gently.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8.

title: frozen hash brown casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, butter, salt, pepper, onion, chicken soup, sour cream and cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: garden zucchini pie
directions: Place shredded potatoes in ice water to prevent discoloration. Rinse well and squeeze dry.
In a large mixing bowl, combine 1 egg, the onion and the Parmesan cheese.
Stir in the potatoes. Transfer the potato mixture to a 9-inch pie plate or a 10-inch quiche dish.
Pat the mixture in the bottom and up the sides. Bake uncovered in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Reduce oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook zucchini and garlic until crisp-tender and cool slightly.
Arrange zucchini on top of crust.
In a small mixing bowl, combine the remaining 3 eggs, the cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour liquid over zucchini. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until filling appears set when gently shaken.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: creamy potato fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler.
Add potatoes, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Blend in sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and knead until smooth.
Press into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.

title: beef 'n tater bake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; pat mixture into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes; remove from oven.
Drain excess fat.
Combine the hot mashed potatoes and 3/4 cup shredded cheese; spread over meat.
Top with 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: patsy's ruston sandwiches
directions: Finely chop pecans, olives and peppers.
Add mayonnaise and season with seasoning salt, garlic powder and black pepper. Spread for open-faced sandwiches or small finger sandwiches.

title: banana and peanut salad
directions: Boil sugar, water and vinegar 10 minutes in a small heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Very slowly pour boiled liquid over eggs in a small mixing bowl, stirring constantly.
This must be done slowly.
Return mixture to saucepan, add butter and stir over medium heat 1 minute.
Cool completely.
Just before serving pour over bananas and peanuts and toss.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Thinly slice cucumbers. Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: famous brisket
directions: You will need 1 large cooking bag and 1 large cake pan or roaster pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: One can crushed pineapple can be used in place of strawberries.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Mash and drain.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix in 2/3 of dressing mix. Mix squash, soup and sour cream; pour over dressing mix.
Sprinkle rest of dressing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Then add vanilla, coconut and nuts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pickled pears
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, cinnamon and cloves. Bring to a boil. Peel pears and cut into bite size pieces.
Put a few pieces of pear in liquid mixture at a time and let the pieces stay about 3 or 4 minutes.
Pack pear pieces in a sterilized jar and cover with hot vinegar mixture. Seal.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, flour and vanilla, mixing well.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips evenly.
Cover pan with cookie sheet (to melt chips) for 5 minutes.
Spread melted chips evenly over top.
Cut when cooled.

title: barbecued meatballs and potatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and form into large balls (about 3 inches in diameter).
Brown meatballs in a skillet.
Peel and quarter potatoes.
Put meatballs and potatoes in a large casserole dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and potatoes.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes until done.

title: ethel's lasagna
directions: Chop and brown onion and green pepper in olive oil with garlic powder.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Brown and drain 3 to 4 pounds of ground beef.
Add all remaining ingredients (except cheese), including onion and green pepper.
Cook until sauce becomes thick. Boil noodles in salted water for 10 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil.
Grease pans and alternate layers of noodles, sauce, then cheese.
Add more noodles, then sauce; top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes, until bubbly and brown.

title: hush puppies(to serve with fish)
directions: Mix and drop by small spoonfuls into hot grease (fish has been fried in).
When done, they will float to the top of the grease. Drain on paper toweling.

title: pecan pie
directions: Allow butter to come to room temperature.
Add to butter, sugar, salt and vanilla; beat well until blended.
Fold in pecans.

title: best chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and eggs until very creamy and well blended.
Add salt.
Stir in flour, mixing to blend well. Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and chopped nuts.

title: ruth gould swanson's apricot jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Chill until thickened a little. Add pineapple and juice.
Beat with beater.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip and mix with a spoon.
Chill again until firm.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Chop onion.
Brown in small amount of butter, 1/4 teaspoon powdered sugar, pinch of oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/4 cup rice (which has been brought to a boil in water or beef stock).
Form the ingredients into balls and arrange in a shallow casserole dish.
Add 1 can of water.
Bake in moderate oven until done.
These meatballs are delicious served with Au Gratin potatoes, Brussels sprouts and a fruit salad.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar thoroughly.
Blend in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to banana mixture, alternating with buttermilk, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours, or until done.

title: golden nectar punch
directions: Prepare orange juice as directed on cans.
Add pineapple juice, apricot nectar and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until chilled. Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Makes 50 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: pecan bars
directions: Beat eggs; add brown sugar and white sugar.
Pour melted margarine over mixture and blend.
Add flour, chopped nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cindy lynn's party punch
directions: Mix all juices and water together.
Just before serving, add chilled sodas.
Garnish with fruit.
May add 1/2 bottle vodka. Makes about 2 gallons.

title: shortcut pickled beets
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients, except beets.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Place hot beet liquid and beets in container with cover. Cool; refrigerate 24 to 36 hours.
Remove cloves before serving.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Add Coca-Cola.
When mixture begins to thicken, stir well and pour in mold or other container.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rum raisin cheese ball
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar and set aside.
Parboil raisins; drain and soak in white rum.
Combine honey, cream cheese, pecans and raisins.
Chill after forming ball.
Roll in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Serve with Ritz crackers or Bremin wafers.
Delicious!

title: friendship cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add eggs and milk.
Sift cream of tartar, soda and flour (enough flour to roll stiff). Roll out dough and cut into circles, put on ungreased cookie sheet. Filling:
1-1/2 c. chopped raisins, 1 c. sugar, 1 c. water, 1 c. chopped walnuts, 1 tsp. flour, juice and rind of one
lemon. Cook filling until thick.
Cool filling, press cookie with tablespoon and then put filling on each cookie that has been rolled out. Bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Stir together the salt, vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Pour over cucumbers, onions and bell pepper.
Let stand overnight and then put in plastic containers; freeze.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and mash sweet potatoes.
While potatoes are still hot, add margarine, salt, sugar, eggs and milk.
Mix all together, then add vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour filling into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes; reduce to 350° for 25 more minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving 1 cup of cheese for topping.
Mix well and place in oblong casserole dish.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: a recipe for living
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Add tears of joy and sympathy for others. Flavor with little gifts of love and kindly service.
Fold in 4 cups prayer and faith to lighten ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of living.
After pouring all this into your daily life, bake well with the heat of human kindness.
Serve with a smile.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Stir in 1 tablespoon honey. Stir yeast until it dissolves and then set aside for about 10 minutes or until volume doubles.
Combine remaining honey with milk, margarine and salt in a saucepan and heat until margarine melts.
Do not let mixture get too hot.
You should be able to put your finger in it without discomfort.
Stir into yeast mixture.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix first eight ingredients together.
Stir in sour cream. Cook slowly until slightly thickened.
Pour into 8-inch pie shell. Add top crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°, then bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: magic puff cookies
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan. Remove from heat. Stir in ice cream. Add remaining ingredients, stirring until smooth and well blended. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: pink freeze
directions: Cream cheese with sugar; stir in mayonnaise.
Fold in cranberry sauce, pineapple and chopped nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch pan and freeze.
Double recipe and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Place berries in a cake pan. Mix well the sugar, flour, baking powder and salt with oleo, then mix with milk. Pour over the berries. Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook vermicelli in 1 1/2 cups broth plus water needed.
Drain and add to the following mixture.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in loaf pan, greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with cream cheese between slices.

title: cajun cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, cheddar cheese, onion, red pepper and Worcestershire sauce in bowl until well blended.
Shape into ball or log.
Toss pecans and parsley on plate.
Roll cheese ball in pecan mixture until completely covered.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until chilled.
Serve with crackers.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook stuffing mix according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients
together well except cheese.
Bake in a 10 x 8-inch casserole
dish
at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from
oven; sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven just long enough to melt cheese.

title: mexican oven omelet
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine milk and baking mix.
Beat in eggs and onion salt.
Drain and slice chilies lengthwise; place in dish.
Top with salsa roja, burrito filling mix and cheese.
Pour egg mixture evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Garnish with radishes, olives or sour cream, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Put aside.
Cream white and brown sugar with shortening.
Add vanilla and eggs.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased uncovered dish for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin pie(sugar substitute)
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 15 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.
This is good plain or with whipped topping.

title: baked bread pudding
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: bombay turkey salad
directions: Cut turkey in 1/4 to 1/2-inch cubes and season with salt and pepper.
Blend all other ingredients into mayonnaise.
Toss the turkey cubes with mayonnaise and chill for at least 1 hour.
Serve on spinach leaves with black olives.
Serves 4.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix with whisk and fill
jars.
Serve over cream cheese with crackers.

title: waldorf astoria fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate; cream well the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add the milk alternately with the dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Fold in the chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° in two 8-inch layers or use large flat pan.
Ice.

title: peanut butter and jelly treats
directions: Heat honey to boiling and add peanut butter.
Pour over cereal and press into buttered 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Melt jelly on stove and pour over top.
Cover and chill until firm.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Kids love em!

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from the pan and drain on paper towel.
Discard half of the drippings.
Stir rice in the remaining drippings and brown.
Add bacon, tomatoes with juice, green pepper and paprika.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes.
Add water or stock, if necessary.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: apples and caramel dip
directions: Cut apples into slices.
Pour pineapple or lemon juice over apples and refrigerate.
Melt cream cheese; add caramel topping and blend well.
Set mixture back in refrigerator until firm.
Dip apples in caramel dip and enjoy!

title: savory sauerkraut
directions: Slice 1/2-inch slivers across the raw bacon and fry until crisp.
Set aside.
Add chopped onion to 2 tablespoons bacon fat until golden.
Blend in flour and tomato juice.
Cook until thickened.
Add Lea & Perrins sauce, sauerkraut, bacon bits and pepper.
Put into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: quick chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is a very rich and delicious pie.

title: glorified rice dessert
directions: Cook rice in salt water and drain off.
Place in cold water and drain again.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and whipped cream. Mix well and chill before serving.

title: chicken filled shells
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Stuff shells.
Arrange in baking dish.
Stir water into soup; pour over shells.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken sandwiches
directions: Drain
chopped	chicken
and
rinse chicken in slightly warm water.
Drain again and chop finely.
Blend all ingredients together well.
Spread filling in buttered bread.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease some cookie sheets.
Melt the chocolate in a small cup or bowl set in a pan of simmering water, stirring until smooth.
Set aside to cool.
Cream the butter and sugar together, then add the eggs and beat until light and fluffy. Add the vanilla and powdered instant coffee; mix well.
Beat in the melted chocolate.
Stir and toss the flour, soda and salt together; add them to the chocolate mixture, beating until completely blended.
Stir in the chocolate morsels.
Drop dough on sheets 1 inch apart.
Bake for 10 minutes or until tops look dry.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients except cheese slices and rolls.
Spread mixture on potato rolls.
Put a slice of cheese on top of mixture.
Wrap each roll separately in foil.
Put in a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 8 sandwiches.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Set aside. Chop lettuce into small pieces.
Set aside.
Drain salsa into colander.
Set aside.
Shred Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Mix together.
Set aside.
Slice olives to make rings.
Set aside.
On a serving platter, layer as follows: cream cheese, sour cream mixture, shredded lettuce, salsa sauce, shredded cheese mixture and olive slices.
Serve with nachos in a bowl on the side.

title: roka lepeny
directions: Mix egg yolks, butter or margarine, sugar, flour, lemon and baking powder together and place in refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart casserole and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°. If you are adding the cheese, do it now. Continue to bake for another 10 minutes or so until the casserole is golden brown and firm. Cut in squares to serve.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Add flour and all ingredients to soften cream cheese.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick; cut with small cutter.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350° until done.
Brush top with egg whites.
Put nuts on top. Bake 10 or 15 minutes more.
Leave room between each one for expansion.
Store in tight container.

title: fettucine
directions: Saute chopped garlic in butter.
Can add 1 can drained clams for clam sauce and 1 carton mushrooms.
When fettucine is al dente (firm), drain and do not rinse.
Return to pot.
Use wooden spoon to mix in 1/2 pint whipping cream, approximately 1 cup Romanean Parmesan cheese and butter mixture (may need more butter).
When I can find extra lean salt pork, I fry it crispy and crumble over top.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix altogether, stirring constantly while cooking.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Top with egg whites well beaten and cook slowly for 15 minutes in moderate oven at 325°.

title: cheesy artichoke bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In small bowl, combine all ingredients, except bread. Evenly spread on bread. Bake 20 minutes or until golden and heated through. Makes about 8 servings.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Spread on cake layers.

title: frosting
directions: Combine Crisco, salt and cocoa.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add powdered sugar in 3 parts.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour cake mixture in and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or test for doneness.

title: out of this world pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple with juice, cornstarch, cherry pie filling, sugar and food coloring.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add dry jello.
Cool.
Stir in bananas and nuts.
Pour into 2 crusts.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop 1 bunch broccoli in blender or food processor.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough mayonnaise to hold salad together.
Chill.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles. Rinse and slice into halves. Cover with hot water and let set overnight.
Drain.
Pack in jars.
Combine and bring to rolling boil the sugar, water, vinegar and spices.
Pour over pickles.

title: grandma's good and easy goop
directions: Brown
hamburger
and boil noodles.
When hamburger and noodles
are
done,
add noodles, cheese packet, tomato paste, milk and butter to hamburger.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: country vanilla ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs, beating well after each addition.
When mixture becomes very stiff, add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer and freeze.

title: raisin nut cake bars
directions: Cook raisins until soft; set aside.
Sift together flour and all the spices and salt.
Add brown sugar and mix in well.
Add shortening.
Mix like pie dough.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix.
Add sour milk and baking soda.
Mix together.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Thin powdered sugar can be put on while still warm, before cutting.

title: punch recipe
directions: Boil water and sugar 5 minutes.
Cool.
Mix jello according to directions.
Mix all ingredients (except ginger ale).
Freeze in plastic containers.
When ready to use, thaw and add ginger ale.

title: sand tart cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and eggs.
Slowly add flour and blend well.
Refrigerate until cold.
Roll cold dough to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut shapes, sprinkle with colored sugar and bake at 325 degrees 7 to 10 minutes.

title: beet jelly
directions: Dissolve M.C.P. and Kool-Aid in juices.
Bring to rapid boil and boil 1 minute.
Add sugar.
Return to rapid boil for 2 full minutes.
Skim and pour into sterilized canning jars.
Cover with paraffin wax or seal in 1/2 pint canning jars.
Cool for several days and then enjoy!

title: autumn pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: nacho style chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl; mix well. Crush chips; set 1 cup to the side (reserved for later). Add crushed chips to chicken mixture. Spoon into greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle with reserved chips. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all the ingredients together real well, leaving enough Meat Loaf Fixins for the topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Last half hour, drain grease and add the topping.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Cut breasts in half; dry well with paper towels.
In large bowl, combine all other ingredients (except bread crumbs, butter and shortening).
Add chicken to mixture, coating each piece well. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, preheat oven to 350°. Roll chicken in crumbs and put in baking dish.
Melt butter and shortening together.
Spoon half over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes. Spoon remainder of butter mixture over chicken and bake 15 minutes longer until brown.

title: microwave cheesy chili dip
directions: In 2-quart glass baking dish. Spread softened cream cheese. Spread chili over cream cheese. Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave until cheese is melted. Favorite chip is Tostitos to serve with.

title: favorite christmas cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
After removing from refrigerator, cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.

Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well. Stir in dry ingredients. Blend well. Divide dough into 3 parts. Wrap each snugly in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 hours or until firm enough to roll out. Dust work surface with flour. Roll out 1 piece of dough at a time to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cutters pressed in flour.
Place on greased sheets.
Sprinkle with colored sugars. Bake at 350° for 13 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on racks.

title: fudge frosting
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Add cocoa and stir constantly until smooth and slightly thickened.
Remove from heat and set aside to cool slightly.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix
Cool
Whip, lemon juice and milk with spoon.
Pour into pie crust.	Chill about 30 minutes.

title: best cheese soup
directions: Cook onion, carrots, celery and hash browns in chicken broth. In double boiler put Velveeta cheese, parsley and milk or half and half.
If too thin, add more potatoes.

title: mints
directions: In 2-quart glass measuring cup, combine sugar, corn syrup, milk and cream of tartar.
Cook on High 5 to 6 minutes or until a few drops of mixture in cold water forms a soft ball (238° on candy thermometer).
Let stand 3 minutes to cool slightly.
Beat with electric mixer until creamy.
Flavor with 8 to 10 drops extract and color with food coloring.
Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto foil.
When cool, store in airtight container. Makes approximately 36 servings.

title: yummy jello squares
directions: Combine Jell-O in hot water, then add cold water in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Add crushed and drained pineapple and bananas.
Return to refrigerator.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar and beaten egg, 4 to 5 minutes, until thick.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Set aside to cool, about 20 minutes.
Fold in the Cool Whip and pour over Jell-O.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate until set. Cut in squares.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over low heat until it makes a ball, stirring constantly. Knead and add desired food coloring.

title: hash brown casserole #2
directions: Mix all ingredients except hash browns, then add hash browns; mix well.
Place in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoons.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool before taking them off.

title: ricey taco salad
directions: Slice carrots, cucumber, tomato, bell pepper, celery, green onions and boiled eggs.
Pour dressing over all ingredients and toss.
Add chips just before serving.

title: california pork kabobs
directions: Trim tenderloin, if necessary; cut into 1-inch cubes.
In medium bowl, stir together soy sauce, oil, honey and ginger. Place pork cubes in mixture; cover and refrigerate overnight or several hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt, stirring in milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Beat egg yolks.
Gradually stir in hot mixture.
Return to heat. Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Set aside to cool slightly.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: In a large skillet or saucepan, saute the onion, celery and shallots until tender.
Add the garlic and cook one more minute. Stir in the flour and stir constantly until browned to make a roux.
Add tomatoes (and liquid if canned) and continue stirring until lightly browned.
If you are using fresh tomatoes, you may want to add a little water.
Blend in the fish stock and reduce to a simmer for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, cayenne, Worcestershire and shrimp.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over rice.

title: blue cheese bread
directions: Mix Blue cheese and margarine in small bowl.
Place about 1 tablespoon of mixture between each slice of bread.
Wrap loaf tightly in aluminum foil and bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: christmas wreath cookies
directions: You will need a saucepan, waxed paper and a mixing spoon.

title: hearty tomato-bean soup
directions: Cook bacon and crumble.
Set aside.
Cook onion and celery in 1 tablespoon of bacon drippings until crisp and tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes. Garnish with crumbled bacon.
Makes six 1 1/3 cup servings.

title: lake francis sheet cake
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add water, cocoa and sugar. Bring to a boil.
Stir with wire whisk until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, one at a time, and mix well.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Saute vegetables and cherry peppers until tender.
Add cumin.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups of warm water.
Drain beans and place in pot with sauteed vegetables.
Add dissolved bouillon, pepper and lemon juice. Cover with water, bring to boil.
Turn down to simmer.
Cook until thick and vegetables are tender.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar and salt and stir in milk.
Add vanilla.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake on lower shelf at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran Buds.
Set aside.
Cream margarine and sugars for 2 minutes. Add eggs.
Continue mixing for 30 seconds.
Add buttermilk and continue mixing for 1 minute. Scrape bowl.

title: collard greens with ham hocks
directions: Rinse ham hocks and place in 3 quarts of water.
Sprinkle with crushed red pepper and cook with lid on 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Slice leaves off stalks.
Place collard greens in cold water.
Wash thoroughly. Slice leaves across into thirds. When ham hocks are done, remove from pot.
Place greens in pot with ham hock liquid and sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Place ham hocks in pot with greens. Cover and cook 1/2 hour or until greens are just tender. Turn gently once so that the top greens are at the bottom.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spinach meatballs with fresh tomato sauce
directions: One half hour before serving, in a 1-quart pan, prepare rice as label directs without adding butter.
Set aside.
Wash well and drain spinach. Remove and discard tough stem.
Chop half the spinach and set remaining half aside.
Chop onion.

title: smoke house californian
directions: Combine mayonnaise and salsa.
Spread on bread.
Layer ingredients in order listed.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together 3 times.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar with electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each one.
Then, by hand, add one cup of flour mixture to creamed mixture and follow with small amount of milk.
Repeat and finish with adding flour.
Put in 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes.
Test for doneness with a straw.

title: apple oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease sheet or cake pan.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend in oats, brown sugar and margarine.
Put half the mixture in pan, cover with apples and sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts, 1/2 cup sugar and dot with butter. Put rest of mixture on top.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts and sugar.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cut warm.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Cook white sugar, brown sugar, Karo syrup and water until it forms a hard ball in water.
Beat in 2 egg whites (already beaten stiff).
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add enough sifted powdered sugar to roll out.

title: baked beans with maple syrup
directions: Soak navy beans overnight covered with water.
Cook in morning for about 25 minutes on low.
Drain; put in either crock-pot or oven pot.
Mix all ingredients except water and pour over beans. Try to cover the salt pork pieces.
Pour boiling water in and cover; stir slightly.
If cooking in oven pot, cook in a 300° oven for 4 to 6 hours.
If using crock-pot cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with French bread.

title: taco-filled peppers
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in the taco seasoning, kidney beans and salsa; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: marshmallow bars
directions: Heat marshmallows and margarine in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Stir in half of the cereal at a time until evenly coated.
Press in buttered baking pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: mushroom-cream cheese appetizers
directions: Drain mushrooms and mince; blend with cream cheese and seasoned salt.
Open package of crescent rolls and divide the cheese filling among 4 rectangles of dough.
Starting at long end, roll up.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill.
When ready to serve, cut into 1-inch slices.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Makes about 24.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Line a 4 x 6-inch deep casserole dish with unbaked pie crust. Fill 3/4 full with fruit.
Mix together the salt, eggs, flour, sugar and milk; pour onto fruit.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and 3 teaspoons sugar together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool.
Cream together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mixture.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until thawed.
Spread Jell-O mixture over cheese layer and chill.

title: christmas and new year cherry cream pie
directions: Soften cream cheese early.
Beat cream cheese and add sugar gradually for 1 to 2 minutes.
Then add Cool Whip.
Mix slowly. Pour in graham crust.
Put cherry pie filling on top.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: gaspatcho dip
directions: Cook spinach and squeeze dry.
Over low heat, melt cheese and sour cream.
Add salsa, then mix in spinach.
Serve warm with chips.

title: the deacon's pralines
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Cook over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to boil and cook 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Add sherry and cook until firm ball is formed in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add butter and salt; let stand until lukewarm. Add nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Store in covered container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all except 1 cup pecans.
Roll into balls; set in the refrigerator for several hours.
Roll in pecan crumbs.

title: pineapple vodka punch
directions: Combine all liquid ingredients gradually to taste (you may need more of each ingredient, according to your taste).
Scoop sherbet onto the top of the punch.
Serve cold.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces and spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Brown meat and onion.
Mix in rice, salt and pepper.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt in microwave oven on High. Stir halfway through. Stir in salted peanuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let cool.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter and press down.
Sprinkle on the coconut, then the chocolate and butterscotch pieces.
Pour milk evenly over all.
Sprinkle on nuts and press lightly.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.

title: party cheese potatoes
directions: Break potatoes apart and place in a well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch or bigger pan.
Mix soup, sour cream and cheese together in bowl and pour over the potatoes.
Crush cornflakes and cover over all.
Melt one stick of margarine and drizzle over top of cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: wiener casserole
directions: Dice bacon; fry.
Add onion to grease; fry, set aside. Quarter wieners and stand around edge of baking dish.
Pour mixture inside of wieners.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with the bacon and onion or parsley flakes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Stir bread, mustard, sausage and cubed cheese into the beaten eggs.
Pour into two 9 x 9-inch disposable pans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes and let cool.
Make scrambled eggs with crumbled sausage or bacon mixed in.
Cut 1/4-inch off of the ends of potatoes and scoop out both ends leaving a lining of potato.
Add your scrambled egg/sausage combination into hollowed out potatoes. Put ends back together.
Wrap in foil.
Place in oven for about 10 minutes or until potatoes are warm.
Fry up your potatoes that you scooped out and serve with your breakfast potatoes.
These are great to make ahead of time and can be used for camp outs; just warm on grill.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls(serves 4)
directions: Boil cabbage leaves in boiling water 5 minutes. Drain. Combine remaining ingredients. Shape meat mixture in 8 rolls. Wrap each in a cabbage leaf and secure with a toothpick. Pour soup into skillet. Add rolls. Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 35 minutes, spooning sauce over occasionally.

title: sister sue's camping cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Stir in cool water. Sift together flour, salt, soda, ginger, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Add dry mixed ingredients to batter.
Chill dough an hour.
Drop a rounded teaspoonful of dough onto cookie sheet, spacing about 1-inch apart.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set.
After cookies are cool, you can frost with a simple powdered sugar frosting.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Peel and slice.
Fry bacon and onions.
Fry until onions are clear.
Add vinegar and sugar; cook until hot. Pour over potatoes and mix well.

title: sweet cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients together and roll in pecans. Serve with apples, cut into wedges.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and cool.
Add vegetables and mix well. Combine rest of ingredients and add to macaroni.
Mix well and chill overnight.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix jelly and mustard sauce and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour meatballs into sauce and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn meatballs in sauce from time to time.

title: old-fashioned divinity
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt. Cook to hard ball stage (260°), stirring only until sugar dissolves.
Meanwhile, as temperature of syrup reaches 250°, beat 2 egg whites until stiff peaks form.
When syrup reaches 260°, very gradually add the syrup to egg whites, beating at high speed on electric mixer.
Add vanilla and beat until candy holds its shape (about 4 to 5 minutes).
If desired, add chopped nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon on waxed paper.
Makes about 40 pieces.

title: real good salad
directions: Drain pineapple - well!
Mix in remaining ingredients then Jell-O. Mix well. Refrigerate uncovered. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Add soup, margarine and corn. Put in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Stir together in a bowl first 4 ingredients.
Beat egg slightly with a fork in another bowl.
Stir in milk and oil.
Pour egg mixture, all at once, into well in flour mixture.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: stuffed pork tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tenderloin lengthwise, just short of cutting in half.
Open between sheets of waxed paper.
Pound to 1/2-inch thickness.
Spread meat with mustard.

title: bambinos
directions: Heat oven at 400°.
Spread rounds with catsup.
Top with pepperoni (any pizza ingredient you like if cooked previously, sausage).
Sprinkle with cheese and oregano over pepperoni.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until cheese melts, 3 to 5 minutes. Makes 4 dozen canapes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Take stems off mushrooms and dice.
Cook with onion and butter.
Add seasonings and bread crumbs.
Mix well with a fork. Put caps in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Fill with stuffing mix.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth. Stir in lemon and vanilla. Pour into prepared crust. Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with desired pie filling.

title: mother's baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight or boil until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Place in crock; bake slowly, adding water to keep moist.
Add milk last hour of baking.
Bake 4 or 5 hours.

title: zucchini corn bread
directions: Mix all the wet ingredients together in one bowl.
Mix all dry ingredients into a larger bowl.
Mix together.
Pour into greased 6x10 pan or skillet.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes. When it is done, place it under the broiler until top is brown and crusty.
Freezes well.
I make a whole pan, cut it into servings and cover it with foil.
Then I take out as many servings as I want and heat them up.
Delicious!

title: hot fruited tea
directions: Use 30-cup coffeepot.
Put spices in basket.
Bring the 1 1/2 cups water to boil and add tea to dissolve.
Add other ingredients in coffeepot.

title: squash au gratin
directions: Wash and cook squash in salted water.
Drain and mash.
Saute onion, bell pepper and chestnuts in butter.
Combine cheese, squash, sugar, mayonnaise and egg.
Season with salt and pepper. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with crackers.
Cook for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: banana cookies
directions: Cream 1 1/4 cups sugar, shortening and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Chill.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture or icing.

title: june's salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients in food processor. Put all ingredients in a pot. Simmer for 1 hour on medium-low heat. Pour into Mason jars and place in jam cupboard.

title: mrs. huckaby's cheese straws
directions: Cream butter; add grated cheese.
Add salt and pepper and flour.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: rick's hamburger balls and cabbage
directions: Make hamburger balls (mix with egg to keep them firm).
Boil them with potatoes and carrots until done.
Then add cabbage and boil together until cabbage is tender.
When putting on your plate, I add lots of butter or margarine and fix cornbread with it.
Great meal!!!

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup of cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover with remaining 1/4 cup of cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add chips and nuts.
Use small ice cream scoop to drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: lemon-pineapple chiffon
directions: Mix together and pour over graham cracker crust.
Cool in refrigerator for 12 hours.

title: great northern fruitcake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and salt.
Add cinnamon, mace, nutmeg and ground cardamon seed.
Stir in eggs.
Add lemon, vanilla and sherry wine.
Add white flour.
Mix lightly.
Add raisins, currants, mixed fruits, cherries, pineapple, walnut pieces, pecans and almonds.
Line pans with heavy brown paper. Grease.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.
Cool; peel off paper.

title: diet cinnamon-raisin yogurt biscuits
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the sugar and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, combine half the sugar-cinnamon mixture, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Make a well in the center.
Add yogurt and raisins all at once, stirring just until dough clings together.
On a lightly floured surface, knead gently for 8 to 10 strokes.
Roll or pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter, dipping the cutter into the flour between cuts.
Place biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with the remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet and cool slightly on wire racks.
Stir together the powdered sugar and orange juice to make a drizzling consistency.
Drizzle over each biscuit while it's warm.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water to soft ball stage, 238°.
Pour very slowly over the egg whites which have been beaten until stand up in peaks.
Continue beating until hard enough to drop from a spoon (it will lose its glossy look).
Add vanilla, right after, start beating and nuts after beating, just before dropping from spoon.

title: orange-raisin rice
directions: Stir cooked rice gently with rest of ingredients in a pan. Cook over medium heat for a few minutes to blend flavors.
Serve warm or cold.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts (if used).
Makes 2 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and salt.
Add chocolate syrup and flour.
Bake 22 minutes on cookie sheet at 350°.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Bake pie shells for 8 minutes at 350°.
Brown ground beef in skillet and add onion and green pepper.
Pour meat and breadcrumbs into pie shell and add egg.
Top with cheese and tomato sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together and spoon into hot grease.

title: easy as pie
directions: Dump the ice cream in the shell; smooth it out very nicely. Back in the freezer for 3 to 4 hours.
Cut like pie and serve. They will never figure it out.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt; let stand 1 hour.
Drain off liquid and add carrots and peppers; mix.

title: chili sauce(100 year-old recipe of grandmother e. ferry)
directions: Blanch tomatoes in boiling water, then peel and chop.
Chop peppers and onions.
Saute until tender.
Add spices, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until down about 1/3.
Put into hot canning jars and seal at once.
Do not let sauce cool off before putting it into the jars.
This is excellent on hot dogs, meat or snacks.

title: creamy potato-onion soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in Dutch oven over low heat.
Add flour to make a paste.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add broth, milk and potatoes.
Add seasoning to suit taste.
Bring to boil; turn heat down low and cook until potatoes are tender.
Mash with potato masher or put potatoes in food processor until smooth. Serve with grated sharp cheese and green onion tops.
Good with corn muffins.

title: parmesan cheese crisps
directions: Roll out pastry into 14 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Brush both halves with egg mixture.
Top 1 rectangle with cheese mixture.
Place remaining rectangle over cheese-topped rectangle, egg-side down.
Roll with rolling pin to seal.
Cut crosswise into 28 (1/2-inch) strips.
Twist strips and place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet, pressing down ends.
Brush with egg mixture.
Bake 10 minutes or until golden.
Makes 28 appetizers.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese and green chili pie
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with chilies.
Pour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Easy to make just half.
May be frozen or reheated.

title: mock chicken roast with cashew nuts
directions: Chop or grind (no blender) in meat grinder, coarsely, the first 5 ingredients, in order listed, in a bowl.
Add unbeaten eggs, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well with hands and add 1/2 of the milk.
Put mixture in a buttered or greased baking dish.
Add milk as needed, but not too soggy.
Bake at 350° until toothpick test comes out clean.
Should be moist, not dry.
Serve with sauce or gravy.

title: pigs-in-a-blanket
directions: Divide layers of biscuits.
Roll wieners in layers.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Soften cheese in bowl.
Stir in picante sauce.
Add lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: turtle bread
