directions: On Cutting Board, finely chop cookies, 2 to 3 at a time, using Food Chopper. Place butter in Small Micro-Cooker|. Microwave eon HIGH 30 seconds or until melted. Mix in cookie crumbs with Bamboo Spoon. Press crumb mixture onto bottom of Spring-form Pam. Freeze 15 minutes.

title: yuletide toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Grease 15 x 10 baking pan. Combine oats, sugar, margarine, corn syrup, vanilla and salt. Mix well. Firmly press mixture into pan. Bake 12 minutes or until brown and bubbly. Cool completely.

title: pound cake 2
directions: Beat egg whites stiffly.
Beat egg yolks in large mixing bowl. Add beaten egg whites, then add sugar, then add melted butter. Add flour last.
Pour in greased pan (angel food cake pan).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix all ingredient together, except coconut.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.
Place balls in pan on wax paper.
Chill and serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese, butter and whip cream; set aside.
Mix vanilla pudding and milk, then mix all together.
Put crushed cookies in bottom of flowerpot, the put in filling and cover top with more crushed cookies.
Top with a flower or a bouquet.

title: pecan turtles
directions: Melt the caramels and milk together.
Add pecans. Drop onto buttered cookie sheets and harden in refrigerator.
(Use about 3 pecans in each piece of candy.)

Melt the paraffin over double boiler. Add chocolate bars and melt; mix with the paraffin. Dunk caramel mixture into chocolate mixture (using tablespoon) and place back onto cookie sheets; harden again in refrigerator. Makes 4 dozen.
Yummy! Good luck!

title: holly wreath cookies
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour with salt and add to butter mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Stir in oatmeal.
(Dough will be quite stiff.)
Work with hands, if necessary.
Roll dough on board dusted with powdered sugar to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with a thin white icing, then outline with green frosting to resemble a wreath.
Use small cinnamon candies in cluster for holly.

title: potato crust quiche
directions: Combine.
Press into 10-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce heat to 350°.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg and milk, stirring lightly; fold in oil.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ralph's chicken recipe
directions: Mix the dry ingredients with the oil.
Spread the mixture over the chicken breasts.
Cover the pan holding the chicken breasts with aluminum foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 70 minutes.

title: old fashioned freezer cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, slightly beat the 4 eggs.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat on medium for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add salt, Carnation milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add 2 quarts milk or enough to make the freezer can 3/4 full of the mixture.
Freeze in ice cream freezer until hard.
Drain water off.
Repack with ice and salt and allow it to "ripen" for several hours.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Bake in oven for 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy and light.
Add sugar, Karo syrup, vanilla, butter and nuts.
Mix well and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or firm to the touch.

title: hot bratwurst
directions: Place 1/2 jar of salsa and peppers in electric skillet.
Add bratwurst.
Add rest of salsa and peppers over brats.
Douse liberally with hot sauce.
Simmer at 250° to 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours in electric skillet.

title: spiced tea
directions: Bring to a boil water and sugar. Remove from heat and add orange juice, lemon juice, cinnamon, and cloves. Put the mixture in a glass or crystal pitcher. Wonderful served hot. Especially at Christmas. But can also be served cold with lots of ice. Very soothing.

title: cherry topped pie
directions: Line 9-inch square pan with whole graham crackers, breaking crackers to fill pan. Combine pudding mix and milk in bowl.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or electric beater until well blended, 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Blend in whipped topping.
Spread half the pudding mix over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers. Top with remaining pudding mixture and remaining crackers.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill 3 hours.
Makes 9 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in the order given.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: company green beans
directions: Drain green beans well and place in a 3-quart casserole.
In a medium pan heat margarine, pimentos, soup, milk and cheese until cheese melts.
Pour sauce over green beans and toss lightly.
Top with crushed Fritos or bread crumbs.
Cook in microwave on High for 5 minutes or in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: pie filling crumb cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with pie filling.
Take cake mix and add butter.
Crumble mixture.
Spread this mixture over top of pie filling.
Cover with sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: western lima bake
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight in 2 quarts of water.
Simmer in the same water until tender (1 to 1 1/4 hours).
Season beans with salt after 1/2 hour of cooking.
Drain the beans and put in a casserole dish, reserving 1/2 cup of the boiling liquid.
Cook meat and onion in oil, stirring until slightly browned.
Add tomato sauce and rest of ingredients.
Mix and pour over the beans while hot.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until bubbly and hot.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: easy fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in double boiler.
Mix in all ingredients except ice cream.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: bacon-date rolls
directions: Cut each strip of bacon in half.
Fry until limp but not crisp.
Wrap around a pitted date which may or may not be filled with a nut.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place in broiler and cook until bacon is crisp.
Serve hot.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half of the mixture into a greased pan, then sprinkle 1/2 of the cheese on top.
Pour in the rest of the batter and top with the rest of the cheese. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy pecan pralines
directions: Place sugar, milk and margarine in heavy saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add marshmallows and vanilla.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir a few minutes longer.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Will be firm when cooled.

title: crock pickles
directions: Mix ingredients; stir until salt is dissolved.
In a gallon crock, lay dill and garlic in bottom of crock.
Lay a row of pickles, then dill, garlic and pickles again.
Repeat until 3/4 full.
Add brine.
Cover with a plate.
Let stand 2 to 3 days at room temperature, then refrigerate in containers.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and place in greased baking dish.
Mix tomato soup, water and chopped
green peppers and onions.	Add this mixture to pork chops.
Cover and
bake
45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican magic pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.
Saute beef (or turkey), and onion until brown.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix. Spread mixture in pie pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and crackers.
Put in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Melt margarine and add to crackers.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup, milk and salt on medium heat until forms a soft ball.	Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until it loses gloss.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 pan.
Cool.

title: prize cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Gradually add to shortening mixture; mix well.
Stir in mincemeat, drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
After removing from oven, sprinkle with a little more grated cheese to garnish.

title: letha's cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well in large heavy pan such as a Dutch oven. Boil until thick while stirring over medium heat.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake at 450°.

title: robert's banana frosty
directions: In a skillet on low heat, add butter, brown sugar, cinnamon stir until all melts. Add bananas until it turns a little dark, then add rum. Turn pan and light on fire. When flames go out, pour on ice cream.

title: bevil salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in 1 cup of boiling water. Add jello and stir until dissolved. Add pineapple juice plus enough water to make 1 cup of liquid. Chill. When mixture begins to congeal, add Cool Whip and pineapple. Chill until firm.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions, drain thoroughly.
In separate pan, melt 1/2 stick butter, cream cheese and Velveeta. Mix in spinach.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter in pan and mix in stuffing and put on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put in a 10 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese with sugar.
Fold Cool Whip into this mixture.
Spread over crust.
Mix Jell-O and water and add berries.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in refrigerator for 10 to 15 minutes when it is starting to gel. Pour over cheese layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Beat eggs and milk together.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to egg mixture and work thoroughly.
Add bread cubes.
Form into 2 dumplings.
Let rise 1 hour (they don't get very big).
Put into boiling water (use large pot).
Boil for 10 minutes.
Do not lift lid.
Turn over and boil 10 more minutes.
Keep pot covered. When finished, cut with string.
Great with gravy.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and gelatin in vinegar solution.
When the gelatin begins to set, add the vegetables and stir.
Return to refrigerator to set.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Sprinkle over apples and bake for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dinner - all in one pan
directions: Brown onions in oil in large frying pan.
Shape steak into balls; add to onions and brown.
Remove steak balls.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cover with water, place balls on top.
Season to taste; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; put in pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin layered cake
directions: Mix together ingredients for bottom layer and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Blend filling layer ingredients together. Pour onto bottom layer.
Mix topping ingredients together to crumb texture.
Sprinkle on filling layer and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: walnut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into Pam-sprayed 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
(This may be doubled for a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake 22 to 24 minutes.)

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels, add peanuts and potato sticks. Blend well and spoon out on wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: no knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and about half the flour.
Beat thoroughly 2 minutes.
Add egg and shortening. Slowly beat in remaining flour until smooth.
Cover with damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally as dough rises in refrigerator.

title: *vegetable tava("bustan tava")
directions: Saute the onions and garlic in oil. Add the tomatoes and sauce and simmer 10 minutes. Season with parsley, dill, salt and pepper. Set aside.

title: kathy's fillings and toppings for kolaches
directions: Mix and cook in double boiler until thickened.

title: goo goo clusters
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Let chocolate melt in oven 10 minutes on 200°.
When melted, add other ingredients and stir.
Add marshmallows last.
Spoon on wax paper.

title: trudy's oreo and ice cream dessert
directions: Crush oreos and mix with butter.
Reserve about 1 1/4 cup for sprinkling on top of dessert.
Press the rest
into a 9 x 13 pan. Spread softened ice cream on crust and freeze.
In a saucepan, mix milk, sugar and chocolate.
Stir and cook until thick, 25 to 30 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cool completely.
Spoon over ice cream and return to freezer.
Top with Kool Whip (softened) and sprinkle with
crushed oreos. Freeze.
Keeps two weeks.

title: baked spanish rice
directions: Brown meat and drain; fry onion and peppers.
Mix meat, onion and peppers with tomatoes and tomato sauce, salt and sugar.
Heat to boiling point, stir in rice. Pour in casserole and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend
oil
and
sugar well.
Sift dry ingredients, and add to oil
and sugar mixture.
Beat eggs slightly and add to batter. Add
vanilla,
fold in apples and nuts.
Grease large tube or Bundt pan.	Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl combine beef,
tablespoons A-1 sauce, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 patties and brown on both sides in a 12-inch Dutch oven.
Drain.
In another bowl combine remaining A-1,
soup and catsup.
Pour
over
patties.
Simmer
for
15 minutes.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Have potatoes chilled.
Then, in a bowl, combine the potatoes with all the rest of the ingredients, except butter.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in a heavy skillet, then add the potato mixture.
Form into a large, round cake with a spatula and brown on the underside without stirring, on low heat for about 20 minutes.
Fold in half like an omelet with a broad spatula.
Brown one side, then the other.
Cut into wedges like a pie and serve.

title: three bean baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Put in remaining ingredients and stir together well.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 6 hours or cover and bake in slow oven at 325° for 3 hours.

title: parker salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water and add orange gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add a tray of ice cubes and stir until jello starts to thicken.
Remove remainder of ice.
Add carrots and pineapple. Mix well.
Pour into glass 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: christmas roll
directions: Cut cherries in half.
Cut pineapple in large pieces.
Use pecans whole or chopped.
Stir fruits and nuts into wafer crumbs. Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Divide into rolls and roll in powdered sugar.
Wrap in plastic wrap and foil; refrigerate. Slice thin to serve.

title: lemon pepper baked salmon
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients. Sprinkle over top of salmon steaks. Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes. Turn once and sprinkle with mixture.

title: camper's stew
directions: Brown hamburger; drain well.
Add all other ingredients and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer until the vegetables are cooked through.
Can any vegetables desired.

title: chilled cantaloupe - peach soup(4 servings)
directions: *Or increased to taste.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together, except the bacon.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Place slices of bacon over top of this.
Bake until the mixture is thick.
Then broil until the bacon is brown.

title: spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart microproof casserole.
Cook on 50 (defrost) for 17 to 20 minutes or until hot.
Remove spices. Serve hot, garnished with slices of red apple, if desired. Cooking time:
17 to 20 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix and make into balls.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Lightly brown hamburger; drain fat.
Add all other ingredients and cook slowly for about 15 minutes.
Spoon over buns.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Arrange 4 noodles on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Mix together onions, cream cheese, cottage cheese, egg, basil, salt and pepper.
Spread half of this mixture on noodles.
Combine soup, milk and wine; fold in shrimp and crabmeat.
Spread half of this mixture over the cheese layer. Repeat all three layers (noodles, cheese, seafood).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Allow to set for 15 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook the onion in butter until soft and yellow.
Add hamburger, salt and pepper and cook until lightly brown, stirring occasionally.
Add green beans, tomatoes and sugar, mixing well. Place in a greased baking dish.
Top with the mashed potatoes, which have been well seasoned, beaten egg added and beaten until very fluffy.
Bake in hot oven at 425° until hot and nicely browned.
Serve while hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt, syrup, butter and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Pour into 9 inch unbaked pie shell.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Note: May substitute 2 pounds crabmeat for lobster.

title: glorified peach pie
directions: Line 10-inch pie plate with a crust.
Sprinkle tapioca over crust.
Spread sliced peaches over crust and sprinkle half the sugar over peaches.
Mix remaining sugar with flour and butter. Add eggs and mix well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until custard is set.

title: cinnamon nut coffee cake
directions: Make filling and topping by combining walnuts, cinnamon and dark brown sugar.
Mix well.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl, cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to batter alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Grease a tube pan. Add dough alternately with topping in layers.
Sprinkle remaining topping mixture over top.
Press into dough with fingers.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 375° or until done.
Cool 1 hour before removing from pan.

title: quick cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine yeast, 2 cups flour, sugar and salt; mix well.
Heat
milk, water and oil until warm (120° to 130°).
Add to flour mixture.
Add eggs; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Cover; let rise in warm place 20 minutes.
Roll dough to 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread with oleo and mixture of white sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up dough and cut into 18 slices.
Place in pans and let rise in warm place about 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake 15 minutes in 375° oven.
Frost.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in an 8-inch glass pie plate; spread chili on top of cream cheese and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes, until mixture is bubbling (maybe less than 20 minutes).
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together sugars, oil and eggs.
Add zucchini, flour, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt.
Fold in 1 cup of nuts. Bake in 2 loaf pans at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil sugar and water; let cool.
Add remaining ingredients, except cranberry juice.
Add the cranberry juice or ginger ale. Serves 50.

title: danish klyner
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, butter and cream. Mix together.
Form into ball and refrigerate dough in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch.
Cut into diamond shape with slit in center.
Turn one end through the slit. Place on cookie sheet and return cutouts to refrigerator.
Melt lard in an electric frypan and fry cookies until golden brown.

title: crab meat quiche
directions: Line a quiche dish with standard pie crust and bake 5 minutes at 400° or use one 9-inch deep pie crust and bake it in aluminum pan it comes in. Combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Beat egg.
Melt butter.
Add butter and cocoa to beaten egg. Add powdered sugar (until right consistency to spread) and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain off fat. Meanwhile, bring 3-4 quarts of water to a boil; add macaroni and boil 10-12 minutes. Drain. Mix pizza sauce with macaroni and hamburger. Place in a 3 quart casserole dish, alternating layers with pepperoni and cheese. End up with cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
In a medium-size bowl, beat butter until creamy.
Beat in sugar until pale and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In small bowl, mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; stir into butter mixture just until blended. Fold in cranberry sauce and nuts.
Spoon into prepared pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes until pick inserted in center of bread comes out clean.
Cool bread in pan 10 minutes; invert onto rack (or will make three 1-pound loaves).
Makes great Christmas gifts.

title: banana-orange treat
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl and mix well.
Divide among six 4 ounce paper cups.
Freeze until firm.

title: farmer's cake
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and cold water.
Add coffee mixture last and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy green chili
directions: Trim separable fat from stew meat, then cut in 3/4-inch pieces. In a 3-quart saucepan, stir together meat, hominy or corn, undrained tomatoes, onion, chili pepper, water, oregano, bouillon granules and garlic.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: international coffee(cinnamon)
directions: Mix thoroughly.
To serve, mix 2 Tbsp. mix with 1 cup boiling water.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Saute onions in butter.
Add sugar, salt, flour and sour cream to onions after they have cooked.
Then add green beans and half of the cheese in the mixture.
Top casserole with other half of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese strata
directions: You will need a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut the center of each piece of bread with a cookie cutter.
Reserve cut out.
Place remaining scraps of bread in the bottom of the pan.
Layer cheese, ham and broccoli.
Place cut outs on top.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, salt, and mustard.
Pour over dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese 5 minutes before removing from oven.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: breakfast hash
directions: Layer first 4 items in a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish. Combine last 4 items and pour over first 4.
Bake 60 minutes at 325°.
Recipe can be cut in half without losing taste or texture.

title: smoked sausage dinner
directions: Brown sausage in oil.
Add onions and apples.
Cook until tender.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine meat, onion, green beans and soup in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with layer of Tater Tots and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese the last few minutes of cooking time.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Mix vinegar, water and egg and pour into the dry ingredients.
Mix until moistened well. Shape into four patties with wax paper between and chill for 15 minutes.
Can be frozen indefinitely.
Will keep 3 days in refrigerator.
Makes 4 pie shells.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Press crushed graham crackers, butter and vanilla into a pie pan.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, vanilla and eggs all together and bake for 30 minutes.

title: great grandma's maine blueberry cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Rub in (can use pastry blender) butter.
Add sugar.
Break egg into cup and fill with milk to make 7/8 cup.
Mix this with above.
Beat until smooth, then lightly fold in blueberries.
The mixture is quite thick, so spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon; bake at 400° in an 8-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Good with vanilla ice cream.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add eggs, flour and salt, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 15-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
When done, spread miniature marshmallows and let melt.
Remove from oven.

title: company macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, process cheese, Cheddar cheese and eggs in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add cooked macaroni; fold in thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: prarieland pot roast
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Brown in 1/4 cup dressing in Dutch oven over low heat.
Add remaining dressing and water. Cover; simmer 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover, continue simmering 1 hour or until done.
Remove meat and vegetables and put on platter.
Gradually add water to flour; stir until blended. Gradually add flour mixture to hot liquid in pan.
Cook, stirring constantly until boils and thickens.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Serve with meat and vegetables.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar until mixtyure is well blended and foamy.
Add remaining ingredients;
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375°F. for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with unsweetened whipped cream, if desired.

title: scotchies
directions: Melt peanut butter and morsels in double boiler or microwave. Stir in corn flakes.
Then spoon on wax paper by teaspoon.
Let cool.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix flour, melted margarine and nuts. Press into bottom of 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: vegetable fried rice
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir together the egg substitute, rice wine or white wine, soy sauce, water and pepper.
Set aside.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Tear off 4 pieces of aluminum foil.
Place 1 meat pattie, 1 slice of onion, sliced potatoes and sliced carrots on each piece of foil.
Wrap and place in a 425° oven for 45 minutes.
Open each packet and put in 2 tablespoons butter.
Melt and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add pineapple juice.
Add 7-Up and ginger ale before serving.
Keep cold.

title: john's gnocchi
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and put into potato ricer (set aside to cool).
Mix the flour and grated cheese.
Add cooled potatoes, salt, pepper, butter and eggs.
Mix until dough no longer sticks to hands, adding more flour if needed.
Roll out small pieces at a time on floured board, making a rope shape.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Drop into boiling water about 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse with warm water.
Pour sauce over gnocchi and enjoy.

title: best ever pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, Karo, flour and butter in a blender until thoroughly mixed.
Add the pecans and blend very quickly just to break up the pieces slightly.
Bake in prepared pie shell of your choice at 350° until done.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter, then add eggs, melted chocolate and flour.
Alternate with milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into slightly greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Top with icing or confectioners sugar.

title: oriental cole slaw and noodle salad
directions: Brown noodles (broken up) and almonds in melted butter; very low flame.
DO NOT BURN.
Set aside.
Mix vinegar, sugar, olive oil and dry seasoning mix from soup pack in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Place cole slaw in serving bowl; mix all ingredients together 10 minutes before serving.

title: butterscotch rice krispie balls
directions: Melt the butterscotch bits and peanut butter together until well blended.
Fold in your Rice Krispies until well blended. Spoon out the Rice Krispie mixture by heaping teaspoon and try to form a ball, then place on waxed paper.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
By doing this, it helps the balls to keep their form.
(I suppose you could also place mixture in a baking pan and then refrigerate.
Just before serving, you could then cut into squares.)

title: eight layer salad
directions: Do not mix ingredients!
Place each layer on top of the others in the order listed.
Cover tightly; use Saran Wrap and foil. Don't peek.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss immediately before serving.

title: country pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Pat beef mixture into bottom of greased 10-inch round pie plate.
Pinch 1-inch fluting around edge.
Set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together first 9 ingredients well.
Add zucchini and sunflower seeds.
Mix well again.
Pour mixture into well-greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 2.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit for one hour.
Arrange in baking dish.
Melt together butter with brown sugar and curry.
Spoon over fruit and bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Serves about 6.

title: macaroon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Then beat for 3 minutes.
Add flavoring and then add flour and whipping cream in thirds alternately.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 300° in a cold oven for 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: crispy chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cornflakes and butter on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: chili con carne
directions: Easy, particularly with a good can opener at hand.
Saute and set aside the onions and beef, using a 5-quart crock-pot.*
Add the kidney beans, tomato soup, chopped tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Cook in crock-pot on high for about 4 hours, then on low for about 45 minutes.
Taste, perhaps adding a bit of sugar if desired, starting with very small quantity.
If you prefer a spicier chili, add a few drops of Tabasco sauce.

title: spiced poached pears
directions: In a large pan, combine wine, orange juice, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Add pear halves.
Cover and cook for about 20 minutes until pears are translucent.
Remove cinnamon stick; cool slightly.
Garnish with orange zest.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: german butterballs
directions: Mix bread crumbs, butter and seasoning.
Add eggs and last the cream.
Mix smooth.
Form into little balls.
Drop in noodle soup and cook until they come to the surface.

title: sunshine punch
directions: In a large pitcher or punch bowl, combine all ingredients except sherbet.
Stir until juices are thawed and blended.
(Top with scoops of sherbet, if desired.
Or you may prefer chipped ice instead of sherbet.)
Serves 18 (4 ounce) servings.

title: sausage roll
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Stir in cream cheese until melted. Roll out 1/2 can crescent rolls (4 to make 1).
Put sausage mixture on and roll up; do this to have 4 rolls.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Slice and enjoy.

title: punch
directions: Mix
as directed; add almond flavoring to taste.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cream cheese bars, except better
directions: Cream cheese is close to the top of Harvest Church's favorite goodies, but the Number 1 position goes to chocolate.
So let's have the best of both worlds.
Holly's recipe calls for 1 box yellow cake mix.
Change this to a chocolate cake mix and we're set.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix everything in bowl but 1/4 cup oil.
Mix well and pour into bread pan.
Put the 1/4 cup oil in pan.
Pour bread mixture into this.
Cook at 375° about 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegi-dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Chill. Garnish with chopped green onions.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk, stirring well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Add 1 cup mini morsels, melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla, stirring just until blended.
Spoon batter into a heavily greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 to 35 minutes, or until cake springs back when touched.
Invert cake immediately onto a serving plate; let cool completely.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Cook broccoli and onions together.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: arlice's jello with fruit
directions: Mix jello mix with boiling water.
Add orange juice.
Add fruit after slightly chilled.
Chill until set.

title: twinkie mousse
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with split Twinkies, minus one set aside. Combine chocolate chips, water and sugar.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating mixture after each one; set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cooked mixture.
Spread over Twinkies.
Let set until firm.
Spread Cool Whip over chocolate mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: bob's cinnamon spiced applesauce
directions: *Gravenstein or Pippin apples make superb sauce.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: Baste turkey inside and out with Crisco oil.
Put pepper mixture on turkey inside and out.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Cook 4 minutes per pound at approximately 300°.
You will need approximately 3 gallons of Crisco oil.
When turkey floats, do not cook turkey much longer.
